WEBVTT

1
00:01:05.191 --> 00:01:06.943
[BELL RINGING]

2
00:01:09.779 --> 00:01:11.781
[PEOPLE CLAMORING]

3
00:01:13.616 --> 00:01:14.701
MASTER:
I warned you.

4
00:01:14.951 --> 00:01:17.829
Did I not warn you what would come
of dealing with Dwarves?

5
00:01:18.079 --> 00:01:19.164
Now they've done it.

6
00:01:19.414 --> 00:01:20.582
They've woken the dragon!

7
00:01:20.832 --> 00:01:22.876
They've brought an apocalypse
upon our heads!

8
00:01:23.126 --> 00:01:24.502
BRAGA:
Come on. Quickly.

9
00:01:24.753 --> 00:01:25.462
Quickly.

10
00:01:25.712 --> 00:01:26.504
MASTER:
Faster now...

11
00:01:26.755 --> 00:01:27.839
...I'm trying to evacuate.

12
00:01:28.089 --> 00:01:29.841
Careful. man.

13
00:01:30.091 --> 00:01:31.426
Never mind the books. Get on!

14
00:01:31.676 --> 00:01:33.887
ALFRID: But. sire. should
we not try to save the town?

15
00:01:34.137 --> 00:01:35.180
MASTER:
The town is lost.

16
00:01:35.430 --> 00:01:37.640
- Save the gold!
BRAGA: You heard him. Get a move on.

17
00:01:39.476 --> 00:01:40.518
GIRL: Da!
MAN 1: Come on.

18
00:01:42.479 --> 00:01:43.813
MAN 2:
Pile them up!

19
00:01:44.898 --> 00:01:46.900
[SMAUG ROARING IN DISTANCE]

20
00:01:56.284 --> 00:01:58.244
We have no time. We must leave.

21
00:01:58.495 --> 00:01:59.662
BOFUR: Get him up.
FILI: Come on.

22
00:01:59.913 --> 00:02:01.915
- Come on. Let's go.
- I'm fine. I can walk.

23
00:02:02.165 --> 00:02:04.501
- Fast as you can.
- We're not leaving.

24
00:02:04.751 --> 00:02:05.877
Not without our father.

25
00:02:06.127 --> 00:02:08.671
If you stay here. your sisters will die.

26
00:02:08.922 --> 00:02:10.840
Is that what your father would want?

27
00:02:11.216 --> 00:02:12.634
[BARD GRUNTING]

28
00:02:12.884 --> 00:02:13.635
BARD:
Open...

29
00:02:13.885 --> 00:02:15.345
...this door!

30
00:02:15.595 --> 00:02:17.096
Do you hear me?

31
00:02:17.347 --> 00:02:18.723
[PEOPLE CLAMORING IN DISTANCE]

32
00:02:19.098 --> 00:02:20.391
MAN:
I can see him!

33
00:02:20.642 --> 00:02:21.643
WOMAN:
Look!

34
00:02:21.893 --> 00:02:23.311
[GRUNTING]

35
00:02:28.399 --> 00:02:29.901
MAN:
Down here! Now!

36
00:02:30.151 --> 00:02:31.903
FILI: Give me your hand.
BOFUR: We gotta go.

37
00:02:32.153 --> 00:02:33.738
Quickly now. Hurry.

38
00:02:33.988 --> 00:02:35.532
FILI:
Kili. come on!

39
00:02:35.782 --> 00:02:37.992
MAN 1: It's around the corner!
MAN 2: Keep on going. man!

40
00:02:38.910 --> 00:02:40.328
[PEOPLE CLAMORING]

41
00:02:46.918 --> 00:02:48.336
MAN 3:
Dragon!

42
00:02:48.586 --> 00:02:49.754
[SMAUG ROARING]

43
00:03:05.311 --> 00:03:06.271
[ALL SCREAMING]

44
00:03:13.862 --> 00:03:14.904
[BARD GRUNTING]

45
00:03:23.663 --> 00:03:25.081
Come on. come on!

46
00:03:25.665 --> 00:03:27.625
Faster! Faster!

47
00:03:29.294 --> 00:03:30.587
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

48
00:03:30.837 --> 00:03:31.963
If only we could take...

49
00:03:32.213 --> 00:03:34.841
...more of these people with us.
but they're hardly...

50
00:03:35.091 --> 00:03:36.551
- Worth it. I quite agree.
MAN: Help!

51
00:03:36.801 --> 00:03:37.468
Help!

52
00:03:41.180 --> 00:03:41.806
[ALL CLAMORING]

53
00:03:43.975 --> 00:03:44.601
BOFUR:
Look out!

54
00:03:47.270 --> 00:03:48.479
[WOMEN SHRIEK]

55
00:03:51.608 --> 00:03:52.400
MASTER:
Move it!

56
00:03:52.650 --> 00:03:53.526
Move it!

57
00:03:54.152 --> 00:03:55.945
Come on! Faster!

58
00:03:56.195 --> 00:03:57.989
My gold! My gold!

59
00:03:58.239 --> 00:03:58.990
We're carrying too much.

60
00:03:59.240 --> 00:04:00.575
We need to dump something.

61
00:04:01.367 --> 00:04:02.035
Quite right...

62
00:04:02.285 --> 00:04:03.494
...Alfrid.

63
00:04:04.621 --> 00:04:05.580
[YELLS]

64
00:04:07.081 --> 00:04:08.249
[GRUNTING]

65
00:04:11.210 --> 00:04:12.337
Faster! Faster!

66
00:04:18.718 --> 00:04:19.636
[YELLING]

67
00:04:35.985 --> 00:04:36.736
[ALL CLAMORING]

68
00:04:44.035 --> 00:04:45.453
[BELL RINGING]

69
00:04:53.336 --> 00:04:54.420
[ROARING]

70
00:05:28.663 --> 00:05:30.623
Poor souls.

71
00:06:02.530 --> 00:06:03.239
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

72
00:06:51.370 --> 00:06:51.996
Da.

73
00:06:52.872 --> 00:06:54.248
TILDA:
Da!

74
00:06:58.544 --> 00:06:59.378
He hit it!

75
00:06:59.629 --> 00:07:01.422
- He hit the dragon! He did!
- No.

76
00:07:01.672 --> 00:07:03.257
He hit his mark! I saw.

77
00:07:03.508 --> 00:07:05.510
His arrows cannot pierce its hide.

78
00:07:06.302 --> 00:07:08.012
I fear nothing will.

79
00:07:21.442 --> 00:07:22.401
What are you doing?

80
00:07:22.652 --> 00:07:24.403
FILI: Come back! Bain!
SIGRID: Bain!

81
00:07:24.654 --> 00:07:25.613
BOFUR:
Bain!

82
00:07:25.863 --> 00:07:26.572
Get back here!

83
00:07:26.823 --> 00:07:28.699
FILI: Bain!
TAURIEL: Leave him.

84
00:07:28.950 --> 00:07:30.535
We cannot go back.

85
00:07:30.785 --> 00:07:31.619
Bain!

86
00:07:49.262 --> 00:07:50.304
[GRUNTS]

87
00:07:54.684 --> 00:07:55.434
Dad.

88
00:07:56.894 --> 00:07:58.688
Bain! What are you doing?

89
00:07:58.938 --> 00:07:59.897
You were supposed to leave!

90
00:08:00.148 --> 00:08:01.649
- I came to help you.
- No!

91
00:08:01.899 --> 00:08:03.568
Nothing can stop it now.

92
00:08:03.818 --> 00:08:04.902
This might.

93
00:08:08.614 --> 00:08:09.240
Bain.

94
00:08:09.740 --> 00:08:10.950
You go back.

95
00:08:11.534 --> 00:08:13.369
You get out of here. Now.

96
00:08:15.830 --> 00:08:16.455
Dad!

97
00:08:22.420 --> 00:08:23.421
No!

98
00:08:24.046 --> 00:08:26.090
[YELLS AND GRUNTS]

99
00:08:28.092 --> 00:08:29.218
[BOTH GRUNTING]

100
00:08:36.142 --> 00:08:37.143
Stop. stop! Halt!

101
00:08:37.393 --> 00:08:38.311
Halt!

102
00:08:46.277 --> 00:08:47.820
Who are you...

103
00:08:48.070 --> 00:08:49.572
...that would stand...

104
00:08:49.822 --> 00:08:51.866
...against me?

105
00:08:55.161 --> 00:08:57.371
Now. that is a pity.

106
00:09:00.041 --> 00:09:02.251
What will you do now...

107
00:09:02.877 --> 00:09:04.462
...Bowman?

108
00:09:05.379 --> 00:09:06.297
You are...

109
00:09:06.547 --> 00:09:07.924
...forsaken.

110
00:09:09.175 --> 00:09:11.636
No help will come.

111
00:09:13.137 --> 00:09:14.347
MASTER:
Now's our chance! Go!

112
00:09:14.597 --> 00:09:15.306
Go!

113
00:09:15.556 --> 00:09:17.892
Head for the open water!

114
00:09:18.142 --> 00:09:19.310
Hmm.

115
00:09:21.520 --> 00:09:22.146
Is that...

116
00:09:22.396 --> 00:09:23.689
...your child?

117
00:09:25.650 --> 00:09:26.984
You cannot...

118
00:09:27.235 --> 00:09:29.403
...save him from the fire.

119
00:09:29.654 --> 00:09:31.155
He will...

120
00:09:31.405 --> 00:09:33.241
...burn!

121
00:09:52.385 --> 00:09:53.719
BARD:
Stay still. son.

122
00:09:54.387 --> 00:09:55.721
Stay still.

123
00:09:56.806 --> 00:09:58.140
SMAUG:
Tell me...

124
00:09:58.557 --> 00:10:00.059
...wretch...

125
00:10:00.309 --> 00:10:04.021
...how now shall you challenge me?

126
00:10:08.859 --> 00:10:12.363
You have nothing left...

127
00:10:13.281 --> 00:10:14.031
...but your...

128
00:10:14.490 --> 00:10:15.866
...death!

129
00:10:16.659 --> 00:10:17.868
[ROARING]

130
00:10:18.577 --> 00:10:19.495
BARD:
Bain.

131
00:10:20.121 --> 00:10:20.955
Look at me.

132
00:10:22.498 --> 00:10:23.541
You look at me.

133
00:10:28.337 --> 00:10:29.505
Little to your left.

134
00:10:31.924 --> 00:10:33.050
That's it.

135
00:10:44.937 --> 00:10:45.521
[ROARS]

136
00:10:49.525 --> 00:10:51.235
BARD:
Bain! Hold on!

137
00:10:58.159 --> 00:10:59.577
[GROANING]

138
00:11:32.485 --> 00:11:33.819
What was that?

139
00:11:34.612 --> 00:11:35.279
What happened?

140
00:11:35.529 --> 00:11:36.989
It fell. I saw it.

141
00:11:40.534 --> 00:11:41.369
It's dead.

142
00:11:45.790 --> 00:11:47.124
Smaug is dead.

143
00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:49.293
GLOIN:
By my beard...

144
00:11:49.543 --> 00:11:51.337
...I think he's right.

145
00:11:51.587 --> 00:11:52.963
Look there!

146
00:11:53.672 --> 00:11:54.673
[RAVENS CAWING]

147
00:11:54.924 --> 00:11:58.636
The Ravens of Erebor
are returning to the Mountain.

148
00:11:59.804 --> 00:12:00.471
BALIN:
Aye.

149
00:12:00.721 --> 00:12:02.181
Word will spread.

150
00:12:02.431 --> 00:12:03.307
Before long...

151
00:12:03.557 --> 00:12:06.352
...every soul in Middle-earth will know...

152
00:12:06.602 --> 00:12:08.687
...the dragon is dead!

153
00:12:09.939 --> 00:12:11.273
[DWARVES LAUGHING]

154
00:12:46.142 --> 00:12:47.101
GALADRIEL:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">You are not...</i></font>

155
00:12:47.351 --> 00:12:48.477
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...alone...</i></font>

156
00:12:48.727 --> 00:12:50.146
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...Mithrandir.</i></font>

157
00:12:50.563 --> 00:12:52.148
[GALADRIEL SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

158
00:12:58.946 --> 00:12:59.864
[ALL CLAMORING]

159
00:13:04.618 --> 00:13:05.494
WOMAN 1:
Help me!

160
00:13:05.744 --> 00:13:07.329
WOMAN 2:
Where's my baby?

161
00:13:07.580 --> 00:13:08.414
MAN 1:
Please!

162
00:13:08.664 --> 00:13:10.708
ALFRID:
Somebody help me!

163
00:13:10.958 --> 00:13:12.168
Help!

164
00:13:15.796 --> 00:13:17.173
[YELLING]

165
00:13:17.423 --> 00:13:18.966
MAN 2:
Over there!

166
00:13:19.925 --> 00:13:20.968
TILDA:
Da!

167
00:13:21.844 --> 00:13:22.678
Da!

168
00:13:22.928 --> 00:13:25.055
TILDA: Da!
- Da!

169
00:13:31.896 --> 00:13:33.814
Aah! Why me?

170
00:13:34.064 --> 00:13:36.066
[ALL GRUNTING]

171
00:13:42.656 --> 00:13:43.866
KILI:
Tauriel.

172
00:13:45.159 --> 00:13:46.160
FILI:
Kili!

173
00:13:46.785 --> 00:13:47.745
Come on.

174
00:13:47.995 --> 00:13:49.413
We're leaving!

175
00:13:50.164 --> 00:13:51.790
They are your people. You must go.

176
00:13:54.126 --> 00:13:55.503
Come with me.

177
00:13:56.712 --> 00:13:59.173
I know how I feel. I'm not afraid.

178
00:13:59.423 --> 00:14:00.799
You make me feel alive.

179
00:14:01.050 --> 00:14:01.634
I can't.

180
00:14:01.884 --> 00:14:03.093
Tauriel.

181
00:14:03.844 --> 00:14:05.387
[SPEAKS IN DWARVISH]

182
00:14:10.059 --> 00:14:11.393
I don't know what that means.

183
00:14:13.437 --> 00:14:14.897
I think you do.

184
00:14:22.321 --> 00:14:24.114
[IN ELVISH]

185
00:14:27.409 --> 00:14:29.411
[IN ELVISH]

186
00:14:41.799 --> 00:14:43.300
BOFUR:
One more!

187
00:15:00.067 --> 00:15:01.318
Keep it.

188
00:15:02.194 --> 00:15:03.320
As a promise.

189
00:15:31.015 --> 00:15:32.891
HILDA:
These are dry. You'll need them.

190
00:15:33.142 --> 00:15:34.143
WOMAN 1: Thank you.
- Here.

191
00:15:34.393 --> 00:15:36.312
Oi! Give me one of them.

192
00:15:36.729 --> 00:15:37.730
I'll catch my death...

193
00:15:37.980 --> 00:15:38.981
...in this cold.

194
00:15:39.231 --> 00:15:40.190
HILDA:
Find your own!

195
00:15:40.441 --> 00:15:42.318
You're not in charge.
Alfrid Lickspittle.

196
00:15:42.568 --> 00:15:43.694
You are wrong.

197
00:15:43.944 --> 00:15:45.696
In the absence of the Master...

198
00:15:45.946 --> 00:15:46.905
...the power cedes to his deputy...

199
00:15:47.156 --> 00:15:49.199
...which in this instance is my good self.

200
00:15:49.450 --> 00:15:51.118
Now give me that blanket!

201
00:15:51.368 --> 00:15:52.036
[GRUNTING]

202
00:15:52.911 --> 00:15:54.204
Master's deputy?

203
00:15:54.455 --> 00:15:56.081
Don't make me laugh.

204
00:15:56.332 --> 00:15:57.416
You're a sneak-thief.

205
00:15:57.666 --> 00:15:58.959
I'll be dead before...

206
00:15:59.209 --> 00:16:00.336
...I answer to you.

207
00:16:01.545 --> 00:16:02.880
Maybe that can be arranged.

208
00:16:07.551 --> 00:16:10.971
I wouldn't go turning on your own. Alfrid.
Not now.

209
00:16:12.931 --> 00:16:13.682
[GRUNTS]

210
00:16:16.894 --> 00:16:18.145
- Da!
- Come here!

211
00:16:18.395 --> 00:16:19.521
You're alive.

212
00:16:19.772 --> 00:16:20.981
[BARD LAUGHING]

213
00:16:21.231 --> 00:16:22.608
BARD:
It's all right. darling.

214
00:16:25.778 --> 00:16:27.821
PERCY:
It was Bard! He killed the dragon!

215
00:16:28.364 --> 00:16:30.282
I saw it with me own eyes.

216
00:16:30.532 --> 00:16:31.784
He brought the beast down!

217
00:16:32.034 --> 00:16:32.868
Shot him dead...

218
00:16:33.118 --> 00:16:34.370
...with a Black Arrow.

219
00:16:34.620 --> 00:16:36.163
[ALL CHEERING]

220
00:16:36.872 --> 00:16:37.873
MAN 1:
Thank you. Bard!

221
00:16:38.123 --> 00:16:39.541
MAN 2: Good man.
WOMAN 2: Thank you!

222
00:16:42.503 --> 00:16:43.629
MAN 3:
You've saved us all!

223
00:16:43.879 --> 00:16:45.089
MAN 4:
Bless you.

224
00:16:47.049 --> 00:16:50.552
All hail to the Dragon-Slayer!

225
00:16:51.053 --> 00:16:52.346
All hail...

226
00:16:52.596 --> 00:16:54.264
...King Bard!

227
00:16:56.141 --> 00:16:58.018
I have said it many times.

228
00:16:58.268 --> 00:17:01.438
This is a man of noble stock.

229
00:17:01.689 --> 00:17:03.816
- A born leader!
BARD: Do not call me that.

230
00:17:04.566 --> 00:17:05.442
I'm not Master...

231
00:17:05.693 --> 00:17:06.735
...of this town.

232
00:17:07.403 --> 00:17:08.862
Where is he?

233
00:17:09.822 --> 00:17:12.324
- Where's the Master?
HILDA: Halfway down the Anduin.

234
00:17:12.574 --> 00:17:14.785
With all our coin. I don't doubt.

235
00:17:15.035 --> 00:17:16.161
You would know.

236
00:17:17.287 --> 00:17:18.497
You helped him empty...

237
00:17:18.747 --> 00:17:20.624
- ...the treasury.
- No.

238
00:17:20.874 --> 00:17:22.000
I tried to stop him.

239
00:17:22.251 --> 00:17:23.127
MAN 5: Liar!
- Cheat!

240
00:17:24.169 --> 00:17:25.087
MAN 6:
You're a mongrel!

241
00:17:25.337 --> 00:17:27.089
I begged. I pleaded.

242
00:17:28.549 --> 00:17:29.341
MAN 7:
Away with him!

243
00:17:29.591 --> 00:17:31.301
MAN 8: Tar him!
- I said. "Master...

244
00:17:31.552 --> 00:17:32.886
...no!

245
00:17:33.137 --> 00:17:34.596
[ALL SHOUTING]

246
00:17:36.056 --> 00:17:37.641
Think of the children."

247
00:17:37.891 --> 00:17:38.767
MAN 9:
Hang him!

248
00:17:39.560 --> 00:17:42.020
"Will nobody think of the children?"

249
00:17:42.980 --> 00:17:43.564
Ow!

250
00:17:45.232 --> 00:17:46.525
MAN 10:
To the tree with him!

251
00:17:50.237 --> 00:17:51.655
[ALFRID SCREAMING]

252
00:17:51.905 --> 00:17:53.699
WOMAN 3: Hang him hard!
MAN 11: Take him down!

253
00:17:54.533 --> 00:17:56.618
Enough! Let him go!

254
00:17:56.869 --> 00:17:57.953
Let him go!

255
00:17:58.495 --> 00:18:00.122
[ALFRID THUDS]

256
00:18:01.206 --> 00:18:02.750
Look around you!

257
00:18:03.876 --> 00:18:04.710
Have you not...

258
00:18:04.960 --> 00:18:06.712
...had your fill of death?

259
00:18:07.629 --> 00:18:09.214
[ALFRID GRUNTS AND THUDS]

260
00:18:09.465 --> 00:18:11.175
Winter is upon us.

261
00:18:12.009 --> 00:18:13.844
We must look to our own.

262
00:18:14.428 --> 00:18:16.889
To the sick and the helpless.

263
00:18:17.514 --> 00:18:19.933
Those who can stand.
tend to the wounded.

264
00:18:20.184 --> 00:18:21.685
Those who have strength. follow me.

265
00:18:22.519 --> 00:18:23.979
We must salvage what we can.

266
00:18:24.229 --> 00:18:25.647
What then? What'll we do then?

267
00:18:30.486 --> 00:18:31.987
We find shelter.

268
00:19:17.241 --> 00:19:18.450
BOFUR:
Hello!

269
00:19:20.494 --> 00:19:21.745
Bombur?

270
00:19:22.955 --> 00:19:24.164
Bifur?

271
00:19:25.457 --> 00:19:26.667
Anybody?

272
00:19:34.466 --> 00:19:35.592
BILBO:
Wait!

273
00:19:36.260 --> 00:19:37.052
Wait!

274
00:19:37.302 --> 00:19:38.428
OIN: It's Bilbo!
BOFUR: He's alive!

275
00:19:38.679 --> 00:19:40.305
Stop! Stop!

276
00:19:40.681 --> 00:19:41.765
Stop.

277
00:19:42.015 --> 00:19:43.267
You need to leave.

278
00:19:43.517 --> 00:19:44.935
We all need to leave.

279
00:19:45.185 --> 00:19:46.687
We only just got here.

280
00:19:46.937 --> 00:19:48.772
I've tried talking. but he won't listen.

281
00:19:49.022 --> 00:19:50.732
- What do you mean. laddie?
- Thorin!

282
00:19:50.983 --> 00:19:53.694
Thorin. Thorin.
He's been down there for days.

283
00:19:53.944 --> 00:19:55.737
He doesn't sleep. He barely eats.

284
00:19:55.988 --> 00:19:59.074
He's not been himself. Not at all.

285
00:19:59.324 --> 00:20:02.035
It's this place. Ahem.
I think a sickness lies on it.

286
00:20:02.286 --> 00:20:03.412
KILI:
Sickness?

287
00:20:04.246 --> 00:20:05.831
What kind of sickness?

288
00:20:08.166 --> 00:20:09.251
BILBO:
Fili.

289
00:20:09.501 --> 00:20:10.085
Fili!

290
00:20:11.169 --> 00:20:12.337
Fili!

291
00:20:42.743 --> 00:20:43.410
THORIN:
Gold.

292
00:20:46.455 --> 00:20:48.457
Gold beyond measure.

293
00:20:51.251 --> 00:20:52.628
Beyond sorrow...

294
00:20:53.128 --> 00:20:54.755
...and grief.

295
00:21:01.428 --> 00:21:02.930
Behold...

296
00:21:03.430 --> 00:21:04.222
...the great...

297
00:21:04.765 --> 00:21:08.101
...treasure hoard of Thror.

298
00:21:15.984 --> 00:21:16.944
Welcome...

299
00:21:17.736 --> 00:21:19.696
...my sister-sons...

300
00:21:23.533 --> 00:21:25.202
...to the Kingdom...

301
00:21:26.203 --> 00:21:28.163
...of Erebor.

302
00:21:31.541 --> 00:21:32.668
Balin!

303
00:21:33.752 --> 00:21:35.545
[ALL LAUGHING]

304
00:21:36.046 --> 00:21:37.297
Kili!

305
00:21:38.715 --> 00:21:40.342
BALIN:
Thank Durin. you're alive.

306
00:21:41.593 --> 00:21:42.594
Bombur!

307
00:21:42.844 --> 00:21:44.179
ORI:
You're alive!

308
00:21:46.640 --> 00:21:48.850
THORIN: Any sign of it?
DWALIN: Nothing yet.

309
00:21:49.101 --> 00:21:50.185
ORI:
Nothing here.

310
00:21:50.435 --> 00:21:52.854
THORIN: Keep searching!
GLOIN: That jewel could be anywhere.

311
00:21:53.105 --> 00:21:55.190
THORIN:
The Arkenstone is in these halls.

312
00:21:55.440 --> 00:21:56.733
- Find it!
DWALIN: You heard him.

313
00:21:56.984 --> 00:21:59.069
- Keep looking.
THORIN: All of you!

314
00:22:00.237 --> 00:22:01.488
No one rests until...

315
00:22:01.738 --> 00:22:02.823
...it is found.

316
00:22:33.311 --> 00:22:34.980
SMAUG:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">I am almost tempted...</i></font>

317
00:22:35.230 --> 00:22:37.566
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...to let you take it.</i></font>

318
00:22:38.608 --> 00:22:39.276
If only...

319
00:22:39.526 --> 00:22:41.236
...to see Oakenshield...

320
00:22:41.486 --> 00:22:42.696
...suffer.

321
00:22:43.905 --> 00:22:44.948
Watch it...

322
00:22:45.198 --> 00:22:46.658
...destroy him.

323
00:22:47.200 --> 00:22:48.535
Watch it corrupt...

324
00:22:48.785 --> 00:22:50.245
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...his heart...</i></font>

325
00:22:51.038 --> 00:22:53.331
...and drive him mad.

326
00:23:22.277 --> 00:23:23.612
MAN:
I've got you.

327
00:23:27.240 --> 00:23:28.867
BARD:
Take only what you need.

328
00:23:29.659 --> 00:23:31.119
We have a long march ahead.

329
00:23:31.369 --> 00:23:32.871
[IN ENGLISH]
Where will you go?

330
00:23:34.915 --> 00:23:36.583
There is only one place.

331
00:23:40.337 --> 00:23:41.379
ALFRID:
The Mountain.

332
00:23:42.214 --> 00:23:44.049
You are a genius. sire.

333
00:23:44.299 --> 00:23:47.094
We can take refuge inside the Mountain.

334
00:23:47.344 --> 00:23:50.430
It might smell a bit of dragon.
but the women can clean that up.

335
00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:52.974
It'll be safe and warm and dry...

336
00:23:53.225 --> 00:23:54.684
...and full of stores...

337
00:23:54.935 --> 00:23:56.770
...bedding. clothing...

338
00:23:57.521 --> 00:23:59.314
...the odd bit of gold.

339
00:24:00.899 --> 00:24:02.984
What gold is in that Mountain is cursed.

340
00:24:03.443 --> 00:24:05.278
We will take only
what was promised to us.

341
00:24:05.529 --> 00:24:06.988
Only what we need to rebuild...

342
00:24:07.239 --> 00:24:08.240
...our lives.

343
00:24:09.533 --> 00:24:11.785
Here. Pull your weight.

344
00:24:12.035 --> 00:24:15.497
News of the death of Smaug
will have spread through the lands.

345
00:24:16.331 --> 00:24:17.457
Aye.

346
00:24:19.960 --> 00:24:22.295
Others will now look to the Mountain...

347
00:24:24.047 --> 00:24:25.674
...for its wealth...

348
00:24:25.924 --> 00:24:27.342
...for its position.

349
00:24:27.592 --> 00:24:29.010
What is it you know?

350
00:24:30.137 --> 00:24:31.763
Nothing for certain.

351
00:24:33.098 --> 00:24:35.016
It's what I fear may come.

352
00:24:46.736 --> 00:24:49.114
AZOG [IN BLACK SPEECH]:

353
00:24:51.658 --> 00:24:53.660
BOLG [IN BLACK SPEECH]:

354
00:25:44.920 --> 00:25:46.296
[IN ENGLISH]
You saw something out there.

355
00:25:46.546 --> 00:25:49.591
The Orc I pursued out of Lake-town.
I know who he is.

356
00:25:49.841 --> 00:25:53.053
Bolg. spawn of Azog the Defiler.

357
00:25:53.303 --> 00:25:56.389
A Warg pack was waiting for him
on the outskirts of Esgaroth.

358
00:25:56.640 --> 00:25:58.099
They fled into the North.

359
00:25:58.350 --> 00:26:00.268
These Orcs were different
from the others.

360
00:26:00.518 --> 00:26:02.812
They bore a mark
I have not seen for a long time.

361
00:26:03.063 --> 00:26:04.606
The mark of Gundabad.

362
00:26:04.856 --> 00:26:05.941
Gundabad?

363
00:26:06.191 --> 00:26:07.192
An Orc stronghold...

364
00:26:07.442 --> 00:26:09.444
...in the far North of the Misty Mountains.

365
00:26:09.694 --> 00:26:10.570
FEREN [IN ELVISH]:

366
00:26:16.159 --> 00:26:17.452
[IN ELVISH]

367
00:26:25.502 --> 00:26:27.212
[IN ENGLISH]
You may tell my father...

368
00:26:27.462 --> 00:26:30.590
...if there is no place for Tauriel.
there is no place for me.

369
00:26:32.008 --> 00:26:33.510
Legolas.

370
00:26:34.344 --> 00:26:36.263
It is your king's command.

371
00:26:36.930 --> 00:26:38.223
[IN ELVISH]

372
00:26:41.726 --> 00:26:43.979
[IN ENGLISH]
I ride North. Will you come with me?

373
00:26:44.229 --> 00:26:45.230
To where?

374
00:26:45.480 --> 00:26:46.731
To Gundabad.

375
00:27:13.675 --> 00:27:15.218
[GANDALF SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

376
00:27:23.893 --> 00:27:25.603
[MUMBLING]

377
00:27:37.907 --> 00:27:39.576
ORC [IN BLACK SPEECH]:

378
00:27:54.174 --> 00:27:55.008
[ORC GRUNTS]

379
00:28:12.942 --> 00:28:14.277
[SNARLS]

380
00:28:16.446 --> 00:28:17.030
[ROARS]

381
00:28:23.161 --> 00:28:24.454
[GALADRIEL GRUNTS]

382
00:28:30.585 --> 00:28:32.379
SAURON [IN BLACK SPEECH]:

383
00:28:43.056 --> 00:28:44.307
Nine...

384
00:28:44.557 --> 00:28:47.769
...for mortal Men doomed to die.

385
00:29:11.793 --> 00:29:13.420
SAURON:

386
00:29:23.972 --> 00:29:25.932
I am not alone.

387
00:29:38.027 --> 00:29:40.363
Are you in need of assistance. my lady?

388
00:29:40.613 --> 00:29:42.240
[NAZGUL SNARLING]

389
00:29:45.118 --> 00:29:46.744
You should've stayed...

390
00:29:46.995 --> 00:29:48.037
...dead.

391
00:29:49.414 --> 00:29:50.832
[ALL GRUNTING]

392
00:30:14.856 --> 00:30:16.316
Mithrandir...

393
00:30:18.067 --> 00:30:18.776
...come back.

394
00:30:28.244 --> 00:30:29.662
[GASPING]

395
00:30:36.211 --> 00:30:37.795
He is here.

396
00:30:38.838 --> 00:30:40.131
Yes.

397
00:30:40.548 --> 00:30:42.675
The darkness has returned.

398
00:30:50.266 --> 00:30:51.476
RADAGAST:
Gandalf!

399
00:30:54.187 --> 00:30:54.896
Gandalf!

400
00:30:55.146 --> 00:30:56.022
Climb on!

401
00:30:56.856 --> 00:30:57.982
He is weak.

402
00:30:58.233 --> 00:31:01.736
He cannot remain here.
It is draining his life.

403
00:31:02.612 --> 00:31:03.321
Go!

404
00:31:03.571 --> 00:31:04.155
Quickly!

405
00:31:06.783 --> 00:31:08.660
Come with me. my lady.

406
00:31:18.419 --> 00:31:19.128
[IN DEEP VOICE]
Go!

407
00:31:22.215 --> 00:31:23.716
[NAZGUL SCREECHING]

408
00:31:58.418 --> 00:32:00.545
SAURON:

409
00:32:24.694 --> 00:32:27.030
You have no...

410
00:32:27.280 --> 00:32:29.532
...power here...

411
00:32:30.033 --> 00:32:32.619
...servant of Morgoth.

412
00:32:34.370 --> 00:32:35.079
You...

413
00:32:35.330 --> 00:32:38.625
...are nameless.

414
00:32:40.335 --> 00:32:42.003
Faceless.

415
00:32:43.004 --> 00:32:46.090
Formless.

416
00:32:49.093 --> 00:32:52.764
Go back to the void...

417
00:32:53.014 --> 00:32:55.892
...from whence you came!

418
00:33:01.731 --> 00:33:02.940
[GRUNTING]

419
00:33:06.277 --> 00:33:07.070
[GASPS]

420
00:33:07.570 --> 00:33:09.572
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

421
00:33:14.869 --> 00:33:16.663
[IN ELVISH]

422
00:33:18.665 --> 00:33:21.000
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
The spirit of Sauron endured.

423
00:33:21.542 --> 00:33:24.003
And has been banished.

424
00:33:24.253 --> 00:33:26.506
He will flee into the East.

425
00:33:28.299 --> 00:33:29.467
ELROND [IN ENGLISH]:
Gondor...

426
00:33:29.717 --> 00:33:30.635
...should be warned.

427
00:33:31.302 --> 00:33:33.346
They must set a watch
on the walls of Mordor.

428
00:33:33.596 --> 00:33:35.139
SARUMAN:
No.

429
00:33:35.390 --> 00:33:36.307
Look after the Lady Galadriel.

430
00:33:37.266 --> 00:33:39.102
She has spent much of her power.

431
00:33:39.352 --> 00:33:41.187
Her strength is failing.

432
00:33:41.437 --> 00:33:42.772
Take her to Lothlórien.

433
00:33:43.314 --> 00:33:44.399
My Lord Saruman.

434
00:33:44.899 --> 00:33:46.317
He must be hunted down...

435
00:33:46.567 --> 00:33:48.569
...and destroyed once and for all.

436
00:33:48.820 --> 00:33:50.655
Without the Ring of Power...

437
00:33:50.905 --> 00:33:54.492
...Sauron can never again
hold dominion over Middle-earth.

438
00:33:56.494 --> 00:33:57.912
Go now.

439
00:33:59.372 --> 00:34:01.666
Leave Sauron to me.

440
00:34:11.509 --> 00:34:13.511
GANDALF: I need a horse.
RADAGAST: What?

441
00:34:14.637 --> 00:34:15.763
Gandalf...

442
00:34:16.013 --> 00:34:17.890
- ...where are you going?
- To warn Erebor.

443
00:34:18.141 --> 00:34:19.684
They have no idea what is coming.

444
00:34:19.934 --> 00:34:20.518
I saw them...

445
00:34:20.768 --> 00:34:24.021
...with my own eyes.
rank upon rank of Moria Orcs.

446
00:34:24.605 --> 00:34:27.150
You must summon our friends.
bird and beast.

447
00:34:27.400 --> 00:34:30.194
<i><font color="#80FFFF">The battle for the Mountain
is about to begin.</i></font>

448
00:34:32.613 --> 00:34:34.615
THORIN:
It is here in these halls.

449
00:34:34.866 --> 00:34:35.908
I know it.

450
00:34:36.159 --> 00:34:37.952
DWALIN:
We have searched and searched.

451
00:34:38.202 --> 00:34:39.120
THORIN:
Not well enough.

452
00:34:39.370 --> 00:34:41.748
DWALIN:
Thorin. we all would see the stone returned.

453
00:34:41.998 --> 00:34:44.917
THORIN:
And yet. it is still not found!

454
00:34:47.754 --> 00:34:51.674
Do you doubt the loyalty of anyone here?

455
00:35:00.475 --> 00:35:02.226
The Arkenstone...

456
00:35:03.144 --> 00:35:05.271
...is the birthright of our people.

457
00:35:06.022 --> 00:35:08.941
It is The King's Jewel.

458
00:35:10.318 --> 00:35:11.819
Am I not the king?

459
00:35:23.164 --> 00:35:24.665
Know this:

460
00:35:28.127 --> 00:35:30.379
If anyone should find it...

461
00:35:31.214 --> 00:35:33.216
...and withhold it from me...

462
00:35:35.051 --> 00:35:36.928
...I will be avenged.

463
00:35:46.270 --> 00:35:48.272
[SIGHING]

464
00:35:52.527 --> 00:35:54.070
Dragon-sickness.

465
00:35:55.571 --> 00:35:57.240
I've seen it before.

466
00:35:59.075 --> 00:36:00.493
That look.

467
00:36:00.993 --> 00:36:02.703
The terrible need.

468
00:36:04.038 --> 00:36:07.166
It is a fierce and jealous love. Bilbo.

469
00:36:10.044 --> 00:36:11.879
It sent his grandfather mad.

470
00:36:13.631 --> 00:36:15.508
Balin. if Thorin...

471
00:36:16.592 --> 00:36:18.344
...had the Arkenstone...

472
00:36:19.637 --> 00:36:20.346
...or if...

473
00:36:20.596 --> 00:36:21.556
...it was found...

474
00:36:24.141 --> 00:36:25.643
...would it help?

475
00:36:28.271 --> 00:36:31.983
That stone crowns all.

476
00:36:33.150 --> 00:36:36.028
It is the summit of this great wealth...

477
00:36:36.279 --> 00:36:37.321
...bestowing power...

478
00:36:37.572 --> 00:36:39.532
...upon he who bears it.

479
00:36:39.782 --> 00:36:41.701
Would it stay his madness?

480
00:36:43.369 --> 00:36:44.662
No. laddie.

481
00:36:46.831 --> 00:36:48.541
I fear it would make him worse.

482
00:36:51.377 --> 00:36:53.087
Perhaps it is best...

483
00:36:54.213 --> 00:36:55.882
...it remains lost.

484
00:37:09.687 --> 00:37:10.980
THORIN:
What is that?

485
00:37:12.440 --> 00:37:13.983
In your hand.

486
00:37:14.233 --> 00:37:14.901
It's nothing.

487
00:37:15.526 --> 00:37:16.777
Show me.

488
00:37:18.446 --> 00:37:19.739
It...

489
00:37:26.704 --> 00:37:29.248
I picked it up in Beorn's garden.

490
00:37:33.252 --> 00:37:35.087
You've carried it all this way?

491
00:37:35.338 --> 00:37:37.131
I'm gonna plant it in my garden.

492
00:37:37.381 --> 00:37:38.966
In Bag End.

493
00:37:41.636 --> 00:37:44.764
It's a poor prize to take back to the Shire.

494
00:37:46.599 --> 00:37:47.934
One day. it'll grow.

495
00:37:49.727 --> 00:37:52.021
And every time I look at it. I'll remember.

496
00:37:53.397 --> 00:37:56.067
Remember everything that happened.
the good. the bad...

497
00:37:57.151 --> 00:37:59.278
...and how lucky I am that I made it home.

498
00:38:08.537 --> 00:38:10.122
Thorin. I...

499
00:38:10.373 --> 00:38:11.624
DWALIN:
Thorin.

500
00:38:11.874 --> 00:38:13.960
Survivors from Lake-town...

501
00:38:14.502 --> 00:38:16.379
...they're streaming into Dale.

502
00:38:17.797 --> 00:38:19.507
There's hundreds of them.

503
00:38:21.175 --> 00:38:23.135
Call everyone to the gate.

504
00:38:24.387 --> 00:38:25.513
To the gate!

505
00:38:25.763 --> 00:38:26.806
Now!

506
00:38:28.140 --> 00:38:29.558
[CHATTERING]

507
00:38:57.837 --> 00:38:59.088
BARD:
Come on.

508
00:38:59.338 --> 00:39:00.423
- Keep moving.
ALFRID: Sire!

509
00:39:01.882 --> 00:39:03.551
Sire!

510
00:39:03.801 --> 00:39:05.219
Up here!

511
00:39:13.936 --> 00:39:16.230
Look. sire! The braziers are lit.

512
00:39:16.480 --> 00:39:17.690
So...

513
00:39:18.816 --> 00:39:21.652
...the Company of Thorin Oakenshield
survived.

514
00:39:21.902 --> 00:39:23.112
Survived?

515
00:39:24.280 --> 00:39:26.240
There's a bunch of Dwarves
with all that gold?

516
00:39:27.742 --> 00:39:29.410
I shouldn't worry. Alfrid.

517
00:39:29.660 --> 00:39:31.704
There's gold enough
in that Mountain for all.

518
00:39:32.580 --> 00:39:34.040
Make camp here tonight!

519
00:39:34.623 --> 00:39:36.000
Find what shelter you can.

520
00:39:36.250 --> 00:39:37.877
Get some fires going.

521
00:39:38.127 --> 00:39:40.296
PERCY: Come on. hurry along now.
BARD: Alfrid.

522
00:39:40.755 --> 00:39:41.589
You'll take...

523
00:39:41.839 --> 00:39:42.840
...the night watch.

524
00:39:51.724 --> 00:39:52.475
BOFUR:
Up it goes!

525
00:39:56.562 --> 00:39:57.730
DWALIN:
That's it.

526
00:40:01.317 --> 00:40:03.527
I want this fortress made safe by sunup.

527
00:40:04.403 --> 00:40:05.946
This Mountain was hard-won.

528
00:40:06.197 --> 00:40:08.115
I will not see it taken again.

529
00:40:08.365 --> 00:40:10.493
The people of Lake-town have nothing.

530
00:40:10.743 --> 00:40:12.119
They came to us in need.

531
00:40:12.369 --> 00:40:14.830
They have lost everything.

532
00:40:15.081 --> 00:40:18.209
Do not tell me what they have lost.

533
00:40:19.085 --> 00:40:21.504
I know well enough their hardship.

534
00:40:22.922 --> 00:40:25.132
Those who have lived through dragon fire...

535
00:40:25.382 --> 00:40:26.592
...should rejoice.

536
00:40:27.927 --> 00:40:28.761
They have much...

537
00:40:29.011 --> 00:40:30.346
...to be grateful for.

538
00:40:35.684 --> 00:40:36.811
More stone.

539
00:40:39.688 --> 00:40:41.816
Bring more stone to the gate!

540
00:40:42.066 --> 00:40:43.109
DWALIN:
That's it.

541
00:40:57.998 --> 00:40:59.208
[BABY CRYING]

542
00:41:03.462 --> 00:41:06.048
MAN 1: These children are starving.
MAN 2: We need food.

543
00:41:06.298 --> 00:41:08.467
MAN 1: We won't last three days.
PERCY: Bard...

544
00:41:08.717 --> 00:41:11.220
- ...we don't have enough.
- Do what you can. Percy.

545
00:41:12.555 --> 00:41:14.515
PERCY:
It'll be all right. Don't worry.

546
00:41:15.057 --> 00:41:16.725
WOMAN:
We need more water.

547
00:41:16.976 --> 00:41:19.311
The children. the wounded
and the women come first.

548
00:41:19.562 --> 00:41:20.729
MAN 3:
Here you are.

549
00:41:21.689 --> 00:41:22.690
BARD:
Good morning. Alfrid.

550
00:41:23.649 --> 00:41:25.151
What news from the night watch?

551
00:41:25.401 --> 00:41:27.945
All quiet. sire. Not much to report.

552
00:41:28.487 --> 00:41:30.364
Nothing gets past me.

553
00:41:37.454 --> 00:41:40.541
Except an army of Elves. it would seem.

554
00:42:13.741 --> 00:42:16.035
My Lord Thranduil. we did not look...

555
00:42:16.285 --> 00:42:18.662
- ...to see you here.
- I heard you needed aid.

556
00:42:26.670 --> 00:42:28.547
[CHATTERING]

557
00:42:37.556 --> 00:42:38.724
Here you go.

558
00:42:39.975 --> 00:42:41.185
MAN 1:
Pass it back.

559
00:42:42.061 --> 00:42:43.187
MAN 2:
Another one.

560
00:42:47.233 --> 00:42:48.234
BARD:
You have saved us.

561
00:42:48.984 --> 00:42:50.444
I do not know how to thank you.

562
00:42:50.694 --> 00:42:52.529
Your gratitude is misplaced.

563
00:42:53.364 --> 00:42:55.324
I did not come on your behalf.

564
00:42:55.574 --> 00:42:58.452
I came to reclaim something of mine.

565
00:43:05.668 --> 00:43:09.129
<i><font color="#80FFFF">There are gems in the Mountain
that I. too. desire.</i></font>

566
00:43:09.922 --> 00:43:13.008
<i><font color="#80FFFF">White gems of pure starlight.</i></font>

567
00:43:13.759 --> 00:43:16.136
The White Gems of Lasgalen.

568
00:43:18.055 --> 00:43:21.016
I know an Elf Lord who will pay
a pretty price for these.

569
00:43:26.981 --> 00:43:28.607
BARD:
Wait! Please wait!

570
00:43:32.069 --> 00:43:34.488
You would go to war
over a handful of gems?

571
00:43:34.738 --> 00:43:38.325
The heirlooms of my people
are not lightly forsaken.

572
00:43:38.575 --> 00:43:40.077
We are allies in this.

573
00:43:41.578 --> 00:43:42.329
My people...

574
00:43:42.579 --> 00:43:45.291
...also have a claim
upon the riches in that Mountain.

575
00:43:45.833 --> 00:43:46.583
Let me...

576
00:43:46.834 --> 00:43:48.085
...speak with Thorin.

577
00:43:48.669 --> 00:43:51.088
You would try to reason with the Dwarf?

578
00:43:51.338 --> 00:43:52.673
To avoid war?

579
00:43:53.507 --> 00:43:54.550
Yes.

580
00:43:55.426 --> 00:43:57.344
GLOIN:
Not a bad night's work.

581
00:43:59.430 --> 00:44:00.681
Come on.

582
00:44:23.370 --> 00:44:25.956
Hail. Thorin. son of Thrain.

583
00:44:26.206 --> 00:44:28.709
We are glad to find you alive beyond hope.

584
00:44:28.959 --> 00:44:30.419
Why do you come to the gates...

585
00:44:30.669 --> 00:44:33.130
...of the King under the Mountain
armed for war?

586
00:44:33.380 --> 00:44:36.258
Why does the King under the Mountain
fence himself in...

587
00:44:36.967 --> 00:44:39.303
...like a robber in his hold?

588
00:44:39.970 --> 00:44:43.057
THORIN: Perhaps it is because
I am expecting to be robbed.

589
00:44:44.099 --> 00:44:45.142
BARD:
My lord...

590
00:44:46.018 --> 00:44:47.978
...we have not come to rob you...

591
00:44:48.228 --> 00:44:50.481
...but to seek fair settlement.

592
00:44:51.106 --> 00:44:53.025
Will you not speak with me?

593
00:45:11.835 --> 00:45:12.711
[CAWING]

594
00:45:28.060 --> 00:45:29.395
I am listening.

595
00:45:30.479 --> 00:45:32.314
On behalf of the people of Lake-town...

596
00:45:32.564 --> 00:45:34.608
...I ask that you honor your pledge.

597
00:45:35.234 --> 00:45:36.527
A share of the treasure...

598
00:45:36.777 --> 00:45:38.779
...so that they might rebuild their lives.

599
00:45:39.696 --> 00:45:41.990
I will not treat with any man...

600
00:45:42.533 --> 00:45:44.993
...while an armed host lies before my door.

601
00:45:45.244 --> 00:45:48.914
That armed host will attack this Mountain
if we do not come to terms.

602
00:45:50.207 --> 00:45:52.960
And your threats do not sway me.

603
00:45:54.795 --> 00:45:56.255
What of your conscience?

604
00:45:56.839 --> 00:45:59.675
Does it not tell you our cause is just?

605
00:46:01.051 --> 00:46:03.595
My people offered you help.

606
00:46:05.597 --> 00:46:09.184
And in return. you brought upon them
only ruin and death.

607
00:46:09.435 --> 00:46:12.646
When did Lake-town come to our aid
but for the promise of rich reward?

608
00:46:12.896 --> 00:46:14.189
A bargain was struck!

609
00:46:14.440 --> 00:46:15.649
A bargain?

610
00:46:15.899 --> 00:46:18.777
What choice did we have
but to barter our birthright...

611
00:46:19.027 --> 00:46:20.821
...for blankets and food?
To ransom...

612
00:46:21.071 --> 00:46:23.282
...our future in exchange
for our freedom?

613
00:46:24.116 --> 00:46:26.326
You call that a fair trade?

614
00:46:28.454 --> 00:46:29.788
Tell me...

615
00:46:30.038 --> 00:46:31.665
...Bard the Dragon-Slayer...

616
00:46:33.459 --> 00:46:35.919
...why should I honor such terms?

617
00:46:38.088 --> 00:46:40.048
Because you gave us your word.

618
00:46:44.303 --> 00:46:46.472
Does that mean nothing?

619
00:47:01.028 --> 00:47:02.196
Be gone!

620
00:47:03.071 --> 00:47:03.947
Ere our arrows...

621
00:47:04.198 --> 00:47:05.324
...fly!

622
00:47:05.574 --> 00:47:07.201
[GRUNTS]

623
00:47:23.342 --> 00:47:24.635
BILBO:
What are you doing?

624
00:47:26.178 --> 00:47:28.847
You cannot go to war.

625
00:47:30.015 --> 00:47:32.309
- This does not concern you.
- Excuse me...

626
00:47:32.559 --> 00:47:36.021
...but in case you haven't noticed.
there is an army of Elves out there.

627
00:47:36.271 --> 00:47:39.066
Not to mention several hundred
angry fishermen.

628
00:47:39.942 --> 00:47:41.401
We are. in fact. outnumbered.

629
00:47:44.071 --> 00:47:45.280
Not for much longer.

630
00:47:47.074 --> 00:47:48.075
What does that mean?

631
00:47:48.325 --> 00:47:50.077
It means. Master Baggins...

632
00:47:53.121 --> 00:47:55.457
...you should never underestimate Dwarves.

633
00:47:59.169 --> 00:48:00.963
We have reclaimed Erebor.

634
00:48:02.214 --> 00:48:03.465
Now...

635
00:48:03.715 --> 00:48:05.300
...we defend it.

636
00:48:23.151 --> 00:48:24.987
He will give us nothing.

637
00:48:26.405 --> 00:48:27.614
Such a pity.

638
00:48:27.864 --> 00:48:28.490
Still...

639
00:48:28.740 --> 00:48:31.243
- ...you tried.
- I do not understand.

640
00:48:32.452 --> 00:48:33.537
Why?

641
00:48:34.288 --> 00:48:35.789
Why would he risk war?

642
00:48:36.039 --> 00:48:37.416
[GRUNTING]

643
00:48:49.219 --> 00:48:51.513
It is fruitless to reason with them.

644
00:48:51.763 --> 00:48:52.764
They understand...

645
00:48:53.015 --> 00:48:54.349
...only one thing.

646
00:48:58.312 --> 00:48:59.521
We attack at dawn.

647
00:49:02.733 --> 00:49:04.234
Are you with us?

648
00:49:36.016 --> 00:49:36.642
Aye.

649
00:49:40.896 --> 00:49:43.315
THORIN:
Master Baggins. come here.

650
00:50:00.540 --> 00:50:02.250
You're going to need this.

651
00:50:03.752 --> 00:50:05.003
Put it on.

652
00:50:10.008 --> 00:50:12.761
This vest is made of silver steel.

653
00:50:15.263 --> 00:50:16.640
Mithril...

654
00:50:16.890 --> 00:50:19.059
...it was called by my forebears.

655
00:50:22.187 --> 00:50:24.272
No blade can pierce it.

656
00:50:35.575 --> 00:50:36.576
I look absurd.

657
00:50:36.827 --> 00:50:38.829
I'm not a warrior. I'm a Hobbit.

658
00:50:39.079 --> 00:50:40.539
It is a gift.

659
00:50:42.082 --> 00:50:43.625
A token of our friendship.

660
00:50:47.003 --> 00:50:49.381
True friends are hard to come by.

661
00:50:51.049 --> 00:50:52.718
I have been blind...

662
00:50:52.968 --> 00:50:54.845
...but now I begin to see.

663
00:50:56.221 --> 00:50:57.723
I am betrayed.

664
00:50:59.057 --> 00:51:00.434
Betrayed?

665
00:51:00.976 --> 00:51:02.811
The Arkenstone.

666
00:51:12.279 --> 00:51:13.780
One of them has taken it.

667
00:51:21.037 --> 00:51:23.915
One of them is false.

668
00:51:24.958 --> 00:51:26.126
Thorin...

669
00:51:26.960 --> 00:51:30.130
...the Quest is fulfilled.
you've won the Mountain.

670
00:51:30.380 --> 00:51:31.590
Is that not enough?

671
00:51:31.840 --> 00:51:34.342
- Betrayed by my own kin.
- Now. uh...

672
00:51:35.010 --> 00:51:38.680
...you made a promise
to the people of Lake-town.

673
00:51:38.930 --> 00:51:40.182
Now. is this treasure...

674
00:51:40.432 --> 00:51:42.934
...truly worth more than your honor?

675
00:51:43.185 --> 00:51:45.604
Our honor. Thorin. I was also there.
I gave my word.

676
00:51:46.271 --> 00:51:48.106
For that. I am grateful.

677
00:51:48.356 --> 00:51:50.192
It was nobly done. but the treasure...

678
00:51:50.442 --> 00:51:52.110
...does not belong to the people...

679
00:51:52.360 --> 00:51:53.612
...of Lake-town.

680
00:51:53.862 --> 00:51:54.780
This gold...

681
00:51:58.909 --> 00:52:00.452
...is ours.

682
00:52:03.622 --> 00:52:04.873
And ours alone.

683
00:52:08.376 --> 00:52:09.961
By my life...

684
00:52:10.879 --> 00:52:13.799
...I will not part...

685
00:52:14.549 --> 00:52:17.844
...with a single coin.

686
00:52:19.513 --> 00:52:21.139
Not...

687
00:52:22.140 --> 00:52:23.642
...one...

688
00:52:24.226 --> 00:52:26.228
...piece of it.

689
00:52:47.207 --> 00:52:48.500
TAURIEL:
Gundabad.

690
00:52:51.795 --> 00:52:53.463
What lies beyond?

691
00:52:53.713 --> 00:52:55.465
An old enemy.

692
00:52:55.715 --> 00:52:56.800
The ancient kingdom...

693
00:52:57.050 --> 00:52:58.260
...of Angmar.

694
00:53:01.805 --> 00:53:03.765
This fortress was once its stronghold.

695
00:53:04.015 --> 00:53:06.309
It is where they kept their great armories.

696
00:53:06.560 --> 00:53:09.062
Forged their weapons of war.

697
00:53:10.438 --> 00:53:12.107
TAURIEL:
A light. I saw movement.

698
00:53:15.235 --> 00:53:17.195
LEGOLAS:
We wait for the cover of night.

699
00:53:18.071 --> 00:53:20.365
It is a fell place. Tauriel.

700
00:53:21.032 --> 00:53:23.201
In another age. our people waged war...

701
00:53:23.451 --> 00:53:24.619
...on those lands.

702
00:53:34.963 --> 00:53:36.423
My mother died there.

703
00:53:38.383 --> 00:53:40.343
My father does not speak of it.

704
00:53:42.095 --> 00:53:43.722
There is no grave.

705
00:53:45.307 --> 00:53:46.766
No memory.

706
00:53:49.394 --> 00:53:50.520
Nothing.

707
00:53:57.569 --> 00:54:00.030
- Unh!
GANDALF: Let me through!

708
00:54:01.406 --> 00:54:02.741
Make way!

709
00:54:06.202 --> 00:54:06.995
[MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

710
00:54:07.245 --> 00:54:08.038
[MEN GRUNT]

711
00:54:17.631 --> 00:54:19.007
ALFRID:
No. no.

712
00:54:19.257 --> 00:54:21.551
No! Oi! You!

713
00:54:22.135 --> 00:54:23.219
Pointy hat!

714
00:54:24.387 --> 00:54:25.430
Yes.

715
00:54:25.680 --> 00:54:28.683
You. We don't want no tramps. beggars...

716
00:54:28.934 --> 00:54:30.226
...nor vagabonds here.

717
00:54:30.477 --> 00:54:32.562
We got enough trouble
without the likes of you.

718
00:54:34.105 --> 00:54:36.608
Off you go. On your horse.

719
00:54:36.858 --> 00:54:38.526
Who's in charge here?

720
00:54:38.777 --> 00:54:39.819
Who is asking?

721
00:54:44.407 --> 00:54:47.327
GANDALF: You must set aside
your petty grievances with the Dwarves.

722
00:54:47.577 --> 00:54:48.620
War is coming!

723
00:54:48.870 --> 00:54:49.996
The cesspits...

724
00:54:50.246 --> 00:54:51.623
...of Dol Guldur have been...

725
00:54:51.873 --> 00:54:52.666
...emptied.

726
00:54:52.916 --> 00:54:53.625
You're all...

727
00:54:53.875 --> 00:54:54.960
...in mortal danger.

728
00:54:55.210 --> 00:54:56.503
What are you talking about?

729
00:54:57.754 --> 00:54:58.838
You know nothing...

730
00:54:59.089 --> 00:55:00.340
...of Wizards.

731
00:55:00.590 --> 00:55:02.842
They are like winter thunder
on a wild wind...

732
00:55:03.093 --> 00:55:06.596
...rolling in from a distance.
breaking hard in alarm.

733
00:55:08.306 --> 00:55:10.392
But sometimes a storm...

734
00:55:10.642 --> 00:55:12.268
...is just a storm.

735
00:55:12.519 --> 00:55:14.020
Not this time.

736
00:55:14.270 --> 00:55:16.731
Armies of Orcs are on the move.

737
00:55:16.982 --> 00:55:19.317
These are fighters.
They have been bred for war.

738
00:55:19.567 --> 00:55:22.195
Our enemy has summoned his full strength.

739
00:55:22.445 --> 00:55:23.989
Why show his hand now?

740
00:55:24.239 --> 00:55:25.490
Because we forced him.

741
00:55:25.740 --> 00:55:28.910
We forced him when the Company of Thorin
set out to reclaim...

742
00:55:29.160 --> 00:55:30.537
...their homeland.

743
00:55:30.787 --> 00:55:32.956
The Dwarves were never meant
to reach Erebor.

744
00:55:33.206 --> 00:55:35.959
Azog the Defiler was sent to kill them.

745
00:55:36.209 --> 00:55:39.713
His master seeks control of the Mountain.

746
00:55:40.422 --> 00:55:42.048
Not just for the treasure within...

747
00:55:42.298 --> 00:55:45.885
...but for where it lies.
its strategic position.

748
00:55:46.594 --> 00:55:47.804
This is the gateway...

749
00:55:48.054 --> 00:55:51.224
...to reclaiming
the lands of Angmar in the North.

750
00:55:51.474 --> 00:55:54.644
If that fell kingdom should rise again...

751
00:55:55.186 --> 00:55:58.773
...Rivendell. Lórien. the Shire...

752
00:55:59.024 --> 00:56:00.817
...even Gondor itself. will fall.

753
00:56:01.568 --> 00:56:04.654
These Orc armies you speak of.
Mithrandir...

754
00:56:05.613 --> 00:56:07.073
...where are they?

755
00:56:11.703 --> 00:56:13.204
RAGASH [IN BLACK SPEECH]:

756
00:56:18.251 --> 00:56:19.794
AZOG [IN BLACK SPEECH]:

757
00:56:31.723 --> 00:56:32.766
[RUMBLING]

758
00:56:33.016 --> 00:56:35.018
[WERE-WORM ROARS]

759
00:56:42.275 --> 00:56:43.359
TAURIEL [IN ELVISH]:

760
00:56:45.278 --> 00:56:46.362
[SCREECHING]

761
00:57:00.543 --> 00:57:02.962
LEGOLAS:
These bats are bred for one purpose.

762
00:57:03.213 --> 00:57:04.464
[IN ENGLISH]
For what?

763
00:57:06.633 --> 00:57:07.926
For war.

764
00:57:24.192 --> 00:57:25.735
[SHOUTING IN BLACK SPEECH]

765
00:57:27.904 --> 00:57:30.156
[HORNS BLOWING]

766
00:57:49.175 --> 00:57:50.969
[IN ELVISH]

767
00:57:51.219 --> 00:57:52.095
[IN ELVISH]

768
00:57:55.098 --> 00:57:56.641
[SHOUTING IN BLACK SPEECH]

769
00:57:59.394 --> 00:58:01.187
[ALL GRUNTING AND YELLING]

770
00:58:08.695 --> 00:58:12.115
GANDALF: Since when has my counsel
counted for so little?

771
00:58:12.365 --> 00:58:14.033
What do you think I'm trying to do?

772
00:58:14.284 --> 00:58:16.828
Save your Dwarvish friends.
and I admire...

773
00:58:17.078 --> 00:58:19.289
...your loyalty to them.

774
00:58:19.539 --> 00:58:22.292
But it does not dissuade me
from my course.

775
00:58:23.084 --> 00:58:25.461
You started this. Mithrandir.

776
00:58:26.045 --> 00:58:29.007
You will forgive me if I finish it.

777
00:58:29.257 --> 00:58:30.967
Are the archers in position?

778
00:58:31.843 --> 00:58:34.053
FEREN: Yes. my lord.
- Give the order.

779
00:58:34.679 --> 00:58:36.931
If anything moves on that Mountain...

780
00:58:37.182 --> 00:58:38.266
...kill it.

781
00:58:41.269 --> 00:58:43.563
The Dwarves are out of time.

782
00:59:10.465 --> 00:59:11.257
You. Bowman!

783
00:59:12.717 --> 00:59:13.718
Do you agree?

784
00:59:13.968 --> 00:59:16.262
Is gold so important to you?

785
00:59:17.055 --> 00:59:19.557
Would you buy it
with the blood of Dwarves?

786
00:59:20.266 --> 00:59:21.309
It won't come to that.

787
00:59:21.559 --> 00:59:24.312
- This is a fight they cannot win.
BILBO: That won't stop them.

788
00:59:24.562 --> 00:59:27.482
You think the Dwarves will surrender?
They won't.

789
00:59:27.732 --> 00:59:29.525
They will fight to the death.

790
00:59:29.776 --> 00:59:31.236
Bilbo Baggins.

791
00:59:31.778 --> 00:59:33.029
THRANDUIL:
If I'm not mistaken...

792
00:59:33.279 --> 00:59:35.698
...this is the Halfling who stole the keys...

793
00:59:35.949 --> 00:59:37.575
...to my dungeons from under...

794
00:59:37.825 --> 00:59:39.661
...the nose of my guards.

795
00:59:42.163 --> 00:59:43.248
Yes.

796
00:59:44.249 --> 00:59:44.999
Sorry...

797
00:59:45.250 --> 00:59:46.417
...about that.

798
00:59:46.960 --> 00:59:47.794
I came...

799
00:59:49.712 --> 00:59:50.713
...to give you...

800
00:59:50.964 --> 00:59:51.965
...this.

801
00:59:56.719 --> 00:59:58.596
The Heart of the Mountain.

802
01:00:00.515 --> 01:00:01.849
The King's Jewel.

803
01:00:03.309 --> 01:00:05.311
And worth a king's ransom.

804
01:00:07.230 --> 01:00:07.981
How is this...

805
01:00:08.231 --> 01:00:09.357
...yours to give?

806
01:00:09.607 --> 01:00:11.609
I took it as my 14th share
of the treasure.

807
01:00:13.236 --> 01:00:14.362
BARD:
Why would you do this?

808
01:00:14.612 --> 01:00:15.863
You owe us no loyalty.

809
01:00:16.114 --> 01:00:17.824
I'm not doing it for you.

810
01:00:19.659 --> 01:00:21.911
I know that Dwarves can be obstinate...

811
01:00:22.412 --> 01:00:23.705
...and pigheaded...

812
01:00:24.414 --> 01:00:25.540
...and difficult.

813
01:00:25.790 --> 01:00:27.583
They're suspicious and secretive...

814
01:00:27.834 --> 01:00:29.377
...with the worst manners...

815
01:00:29.627 --> 01:00:31.671
...imaginable.
but they are also brave...

816
01:00:31.921 --> 01:00:33.172
...and kind...

817
01:00:34.757 --> 01:00:36.092
...and loyal to a fault.

818
01:00:37.260 --> 01:00:38.094
I've grown...

819
01:00:38.344 --> 01:00:41.055
...very fond of them.
and I would save them if I can.

820
01:00:41.889 --> 01:00:42.932
Now. Thorin...

821
01:00:43.182 --> 01:00:45.435
...values this stone above all else.

822
01:00:45.685 --> 01:00:48.062
In exchange for its return.
he will give you...

823
01:00:48.313 --> 01:00:49.397
...what you are owed.

824
01:00:49.647 --> 01:00:50.606
There will be no need...

825
01:00:50.857 --> 01:00:51.774
...for war.

826
01:00:57.280 --> 01:00:58.281
GANDALF:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Rest up tonight.</i></font>

827
01:00:58.531 --> 01:01:01.200
- You must leave on the morrow.
- What?

828
01:01:01.451 --> 01:01:04.370
- Get as far away from here as possible.
- I'm not leaving.

829
01:01:04.620 --> 01:01:07.373
You picked me as the 14th man.
I'm not leaving the Company.

830
01:01:07.623 --> 01:01:09.625
There is no Company. Not anymore.

831
01:01:09.876 --> 01:01:12.337
Imagine what Thorin will do
when he finds out what you've done.

832
01:01:12.587 --> 01:01:14.172
I'm not afraid of Thorin.

833
01:01:14.422 --> 01:01:15.715
Well. you should be.

834
01:01:16.299 --> 01:01:17.300
Don't underestimate...

835
01:01:17.550 --> 01:01:19.469
...the evil of gold.

836
01:01:19.719 --> 01:01:20.720
Gold over which...

837
01:01:20.970 --> 01:01:23.056
...a serpent has long brooded.

838
01:01:23.306 --> 01:01:25.850
Dragon-sickness seeps
into the hearts of all...

839
01:01:26.100 --> 01:01:27.769
...who come near this Mountain.

840
01:01:29.395 --> 01:01:30.396
Almost all. Heh.

841
01:01:33.274 --> 01:01:34.567
You there.

842
01:01:34.817 --> 01:01:35.902
Find this Hobbit a bed...

843
01:01:37.070 --> 01:01:38.821
...and fill his belly with hot food.

844
01:01:40.782 --> 01:01:41.991
He's earned it.

845
01:01:44.285 --> 01:01:44.911
Hey.

846
01:01:46.079 --> 01:01:47.080
Keep an eye on him.

847
01:01:47.872 --> 01:01:48.873
If he should try...

848
01:01:49.123 --> 01:01:50.958
...to leave. you tell me.

849
01:01:53.795 --> 01:01:54.670
ALFRID:
Move it!

850
01:01:54.921 --> 01:01:56.506
Stupid Hobbit.

851
01:02:30.248 --> 01:02:33.209
Wakey-wakey. Hobbit. Up you get.

852
01:02:55.648 --> 01:02:57.358
I will put the next one between your eyes.

853
01:02:57.608 --> 01:02:59.652
[ALL SHOUTING]

854
01:03:22.341 --> 01:03:23.634
We have come to tell you...

855
01:03:23.885 --> 01:03:27.138
...payment of your debt has been offered...

856
01:03:27.388 --> 01:03:28.848
...and accepted.

857
01:03:30.308 --> 01:03:31.309
THORIN:
What payment?

858
01:03:32.477 --> 01:03:33.769
I gave you nothing.

859
01:03:34.520 --> 01:03:36.272
You have nothing.

860
01:03:43.196 --> 01:03:44.655
We have this.

861
01:03:48.534 --> 01:03:49.952
KILI:
They have the Arkenstone.

862
01:03:51.579 --> 01:03:52.705
Thieves!

863
01:03:53.331 --> 01:03:56.459
How came you by the heirloom
of our house?

864
01:03:56.709 --> 01:03:58.211
That stone belongs to the king!

865
01:03:59.795 --> 01:04:01.047
And the king may have it...

866
01:04:01.923 --> 01:04:03.424
...with our goodwill.

867
01:04:08.346 --> 01:04:12.308
But first he must honor his word.

868
01:04:14.769 --> 01:04:16.479
They are taking us for fools.

869
01:04:18.189 --> 01:04:19.565
This is a ruse.

870
01:04:21.150 --> 01:04:22.902
A filthy lie.

871
01:04:24.237 --> 01:04:27.156
The Arkenstone is in this Mountain!

872
01:04:27.406 --> 01:04:28.533
It is a trick!

873
01:04:28.783 --> 01:04:30.409
BILBO:
It's no trick.

874
01:04:31.577 --> 01:04:32.870
The stone is real.

875
01:04:34.413 --> 01:04:35.998
I gave it to them.

876
01:04:44.215 --> 01:04:45.049
You?

877
01:04:47.593 --> 01:04:49.804
I took it as my 14th share.

878
01:04:51.681 --> 01:04:53.516
You would steal from me?

879
01:04:53.766 --> 01:04:54.934
Steal from you? No.

880
01:04:55.184 --> 01:04:58.396
No. I may be a burglar.
but I like to think I'm an honest one.

881
01:05:01.607 --> 01:05:03.526
I'll let it stand against my claim.

882
01:05:04.026 --> 01:05:05.820
Against your claim?

883
01:05:07.572 --> 01:05:09.240
Your claim.

884
01:05:10.116 --> 01:05:13.077
You have no claim over me.
you miserable rat!

885
01:05:15.621 --> 01:05:17.498
I was going to give it to you.

886
01:05:18.499 --> 01:05:21.460
- Many times I wanted to. but...
- But what...

887
01:05:21.711 --> 01:05:23.004
...thief?

888
01:05:23.588 --> 01:05:25.506
You are changed. Thorin.

889
01:05:25.756 --> 01:05:26.757
The Dwarf I met...

890
01:05:27.008 --> 01:05:29.885
...in Bag End would never have
gone back on his word.

891
01:05:30.136 --> 01:05:31.387
Would never have doubted...

892
01:05:31.637 --> 01:05:33.180
...the loyalty of his kin!

893
01:05:33.931 --> 01:05:36.183
Do not speak to me...

894
01:05:36.892 --> 01:05:38.227
...of loyalty.

895
01:05:41.814 --> 01:05:43.065
Throw him from the rampart!

896
01:05:52.325 --> 01:05:53.367
Did you not hear me?

897
01:05:56.954 --> 01:05:58.748
I will do it myself. Curse you!

898
01:05:59.999 --> 01:06:00.583
No!

899
01:06:00.833 --> 01:06:02.084
Cursed be the Wizard...

900
01:06:02.335 --> 01:06:05.171
- ...that forced you on us!
- If you don't like my burglar...

901
01:06:05.421 --> 01:06:06.297
...then please...

902
01:06:06.547 --> 01:06:07.423
...don't damage him.

903
01:06:07.673 --> 01:06:08.924
Return him to me.

904
01:06:13.763 --> 01:06:17.767
You're not making a very splendid figure
as King under the Mountain...

905
01:06:18.017 --> 01:06:21.854
...are you. Thorin...

906
01:06:22.104 --> 01:06:23.272
...son of Thrain?

907
01:06:30.196 --> 01:06:32.406
THORIN: Never again will I have dealings
with Wizards!

908
01:06:32.657 --> 01:06:33.240
Go.

909
01:06:33.491 --> 01:06:34.367
Or Shire rats!

910
01:06:39.413 --> 01:06:41.040
BARD:
Are we resolved?

911
01:06:41.999 --> 01:06:43.000
The return...

912
01:06:43.250 --> 01:06:45.211
...of the Arkenstone
for what was promised?

913
01:06:51.509 --> 01:06:53.219
Give us your answer.

914
01:06:54.470 --> 01:06:56.055
Will you have peace...

915
01:06:57.807 --> 01:06:59.141
...or war?

916
01:07:01.560 --> 01:07:03.062
[CAWS]

917
01:07:10.695 --> 01:07:12.613
I will have war.

918
01:07:14.990 --> 01:07:16.701
[RUMBLING]

919
01:07:25.543 --> 01:07:27.211
Ironfoot.

920
01:07:30.506 --> 01:07:32.258
[ALL SHOUTING]

921
01:07:34.343 --> 01:07:35.344
[SHOUTS IN ELVISH]

922
01:07:54.447 --> 01:07:55.573
Who is that?

923
01:07:56.115 --> 01:07:57.366
He doesn't look very happy.

924
01:07:57.616 --> 01:08:00.369
It is Dain. Lord of the Iron Hills.

925
01:08:00.619 --> 01:08:01.454
Thorin's...

926
01:08:01.704 --> 01:08:03.330
- ...cousin.
- Are they alike?

927
01:08:04.415 --> 01:08:08.043
I've always found Thorin
the more reasonable of the two.

928
01:08:18.304 --> 01:08:19.430
DAIN:
Good morning.

929
01:08:19.680 --> 01:08:21.223
How are we all?

930
01:08:24.810 --> 01:08:26.187
I have a wee proposition...

931
01:08:26.437 --> 01:08:28.731
...if you wouldn't mind giving me
a few moments...

932
01:08:28.981 --> 01:08:30.232
...of your time.

933
01:08:31.484 --> 01:08:33.527
Would you consider...

934
01:08:35.529 --> 01:08:36.781
...just sodding off?

935
01:08:38.115 --> 01:08:39.116
All of you!

936
01:08:39.366 --> 01:08:40.826
Right now!

937
01:08:41.076 --> 01:08:41.994
Stand fast.

938
01:08:43.829 --> 01:08:45.080
Come now. Lord Dain.

939
01:08:46.040 --> 01:08:47.625
Gandalf the Grey.

940
01:08:49.543 --> 01:08:50.669
Tell this rabble...

941
01:08:50.920 --> 01:08:52.755
...to leave. or I'll water...

942
01:08:53.005 --> 01:08:54.673
...the ground with their blood!

943
01:08:58.177 --> 01:08:59.303
No need for war...

944
01:08:59.553 --> 01:09:02.223
...between Dwarves. Men and Elves.

945
01:09:02.473 --> 01:09:03.474
A legion of Orcs...

946
01:09:03.724 --> 01:09:05.267
...march on the Mountain.

947
01:09:05.518 --> 01:09:06.227
Stand down.

948
01:09:06.477 --> 01:09:09.522
I will not stand down before any Elf.

949
01:09:10.231 --> 01:09:13.234
Not least this faithless Woodland sprite.

950
01:09:14.235 --> 01:09:17.279
He wishes nothing but ill upon my people.

951
01:09:18.364 --> 01:09:19.365
If he chooses...

952
01:09:19.615 --> 01:09:22.284
...to stand between me and my kin...

953
01:09:23.577 --> 01:09:25.454
...I'll split his pretty head open!

954
01:09:25.704 --> 01:09:27.540
See if he's still smirking then.

955
01:09:27.790 --> 01:09:29.542
[ALL SHOUTING]

956
01:09:30.167 --> 01:09:32.962
He's clearly mad. like his cousin.

957
01:09:33.212 --> 01:09:35.714
You hear that. lads? We're on!

958
01:09:35.965 --> 01:09:39.134
Let's give these bastards
a good hammering!

959
01:09:39.385 --> 01:09:40.928
[SHOUTING IN DWARVISH]

960
01:09:41.887 --> 01:09:43.514
[ALL SHOUTING]

961
01:09:51.522 --> 01:09:53.190
[RUMBLING]

962
01:09:58.612 --> 01:10:00.489
Were-worms.

963
01:10:01.824 --> 01:10:03.534
[ROARING]

964
01:10:08.998 --> 01:10:11.250
Oh. come on.

965
01:10:17.339 --> 01:10:18.340
[ORCS SHOUTING IN BLACK SPEECH]

966
01:10:24.680 --> 01:10:26.432
[IN BLACK SPEECH]

967
01:10:28.767 --> 01:10:31.020
[HORN BLOWING]

968
01:10:39.361 --> 01:10:40.905
The hordes of hell are upon us!

969
01:10:41.989 --> 01:10:45.451
To battle! To battle. sons of Durin!

970
01:10:45.701 --> 01:10:47.703
[ALL GRUNTING AND SNARLING]

971
01:10:51.081 --> 01:10:53.208
FILI: I'm going over the wall.
Who's coming with me?

972
01:10:53.459 --> 01:10:55.419
OIN: Aye!
DWALIN: Come on. let's go!

973
01:10:55.669 --> 01:10:57.338
THORIN: Stand down.
ORI: What?

974
01:10:57.588 --> 01:10:59.089
Are we to do nothing?

975
01:10:59.340 --> 01:11:01.008
I said. stand down!

976
01:11:05.846 --> 01:11:06.972
The Elves.

977
01:11:07.222 --> 01:11:08.849
Will they not fight?

978
01:11:11.769 --> 01:11:12.770
GANDALF:
Thranduil!

979
01:11:13.020 --> 01:11:14.396
This is madness!

980
01:11:31.622 --> 01:11:32.539
[SHOUTING IN DWARVISH]

981
01:12:03.278 --> 01:12:04.279
DAIN:
Charge!

982
01:12:04.530 --> 01:12:05.406
Yes!

983
01:12:06.448 --> 01:12:07.658
[SPEAKING IN DWARVISH]

984
01:12:09.743 --> 01:12:10.828
BILBO:
Uh. Gandalf?

985
01:12:11.078 --> 01:12:12.705
Is this a good place to stand?

986
01:12:13.288 --> 01:12:14.540
[IN BLACK SPEECH]

987
01:12:15.916 --> 01:12:17.793
[HORN BLOWING]

988
01:12:27.052 --> 01:12:28.053
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

989
01:12:41.400 --> 01:12:42.526
[HORN BLOWING]

990
01:12:44.236 --> 01:12:45.654
[ORC SHOUTING IN BLACK SPEECH]

991
01:12:47.322 --> 01:12:48.532
[ALL SHOUTING IN CADENCE]

992
01:12:55.664 --> 01:12:57.041
Azog.

993
01:12:58.542 --> 01:13:00.669
He's trying to cut us off.

994
01:13:04.923 --> 01:13:05.924
BARD:
All of you!

995
01:13:06.175 --> 01:13:08.093
Fall back to Dale!

996
01:13:08.343 --> 01:13:09.470
Now!

997
01:13:12.389 --> 01:13:13.515
GANDALF:
To the city!

998
01:13:13.766 --> 01:13:15.809
Bilbo! This way!

999
01:13:18.687 --> 01:13:20.147
[GRUNTING AND SNARLING]

1000
01:13:31.158 --> 01:13:32.284
[TROLLS ROAR]

1001
01:13:51.929 --> 01:13:53.222
[ROARS]

1002
01:13:57.101 --> 01:13:59.103
[ALL SHOUTING]

1003
01:14:10.572 --> 01:14:11.740
[PEOPLE CLAMORING
AND SCREAMING]

1004
01:14:26.421 --> 01:14:27.673
Sigrid!

1005
01:14:28.590 --> 01:14:29.591
Tilda!

1006
01:14:39.685 --> 01:14:41.895
My children! Where are my children?

1007
01:14:42.146 --> 01:14:45.065
I saw them!
They were down in the old market!

1008
01:14:45.315 --> 01:14:46.525
The market?

1009
01:14:47.025 --> 01:14:48.443
Where are they now?

1010
01:14:48.694 --> 01:14:50.279
Tilda! Sigrid!

1011
01:14:50.529 --> 01:14:53.198
Bard! Orcs are storming over the causeway!

1012
01:14:54.116 --> 01:14:57.452
Get the bowmen to the eastern parapet.
Hold them off as long as you can.

1013
01:14:57.703 --> 01:14:59.705
Archers! This way!

1014
01:14:59.955 --> 01:15:02.166
The Orcs have taken Stone Street!

1015
01:15:02.416 --> 01:15:04.126
The market's overrun!

1016
01:15:07.421 --> 01:15:08.964
The rest of you...

1017
01:15:09.214 --> 01:15:10.549
...follow me!

1018
01:15:19.016 --> 01:15:20.350
[ALL SHOUTING]

1019
01:15:32.738 --> 01:15:34.239
ALFRID:
Charge! Onward!

1020
01:15:35.115 --> 01:15:36.658
To the death!

1021
01:15:52.007 --> 01:15:53.258
[SCREAMING]

1022
01:16:07.898 --> 01:16:08.565
SIGRID:
Da!

1023
01:16:08.815 --> 01:16:09.733
BOTH:
Da!

1024
01:16:09.983 --> 01:16:11.860
BAIN: Here!
TILDA: We're down here!

1025
01:16:21.453 --> 01:16:23.163
[SNARLS]

1026
01:16:23.413 --> 01:16:24.206
[SCREAMING]

1027
01:16:40.138 --> 01:16:41.014
BARD:
Bain!

1028
01:16:41.932 --> 01:16:42.683
Sigrid! Get down!

1029
01:16:47.771 --> 01:16:48.647
[GRUNTING]

1030
01:17:03.370 --> 01:17:04.371
Listen!

1031
01:17:04.621 --> 01:17:05.247
Gather...

1032
01:17:05.497 --> 01:17:06.707
...the women and children.

1033
01:17:06.957 --> 01:17:08.458
Take them to the Great Hall...

1034
01:17:08.709 --> 01:17:10.294
...and barricade the door.

1035
01:17:10.544 --> 01:17:11.795
You understand?

1036
01:17:12.546 --> 01:17:14.256
You must not come out for any reason.

1037
01:17:14.506 --> 01:17:15.799
We want to stay with you!

1038
01:17:16.049 --> 01:17:18.260
Show your father some respect.

1039
01:17:18.844 --> 01:17:19.845
You leave it to me...

1040
01:17:20.095 --> 01:17:20.679
...sire.

1041
01:17:20.929 --> 01:17:22.180
You heard him.

1042
01:17:22.431 --> 01:17:24.224
- We make for the Great Hall.
- Alfrid!

1043
01:17:25.600 --> 01:17:26.852
Women and children only.

1044
01:17:27.102 --> 01:17:28.020
I need every man...

1045
01:17:28.270 --> 01:17:28.937
...fighting.

1046
01:17:29.187 --> 01:17:30.480
See that you return.

1047
01:17:30.731 --> 01:17:32.107
I'll get them to safety. sire.

1048
01:17:34.776 --> 01:17:37.112
Then my sword is yours to command.
Get up!

1049
01:17:38.530 --> 01:17:39.823
Look after them.

1050
01:17:43.493 --> 01:17:44.911
Shift it. granny!

1051
01:17:57.174 --> 01:17:58.216
Make for the Great Hall!

1052
01:18:01.595 --> 01:18:02.763
ALFRID:
Out of my way!

1053
01:18:03.013 --> 01:18:04.973
Abandon the cripples!

1054
01:18:27.954 --> 01:18:29.414
[ORCS GROWLING]

1055
01:18:51.395 --> 01:18:52.396
[IN BLACK SPEECH]

1056
01:19:06.201 --> 01:19:07.202
You buggers!

1057
01:19:20.632 --> 01:19:22.008
Where's Thorin?

1058
01:19:23.343 --> 01:19:25.303
We need him! Where is he?

1059
01:19:29.224 --> 01:19:31.184
[IN BLACK SPEECH]

1060
01:19:37.107 --> 01:19:38.316
[HORN BLOWING]

1061
01:19:38.567 --> 01:19:40.402
Fall back!

1062
01:20:06.344 --> 01:20:07.637
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1063
01:20:09.055 --> 01:20:10.891
DWALIN:
Since when do we forsake...

1064
01:20:11.141 --> 01:20:12.309
...our own people?

1065
01:20:12.559 --> 01:20:13.393
Thorin...

1066
01:20:14.311 --> 01:20:15.312
...they are dying...

1067
01:20:15.562 --> 01:20:16.730
...out there.

1068
01:20:22.068 --> 01:20:25.322
There are halls beneath halls
within this Mountain.

1069
01:20:27.449 --> 01:20:29.576
Places we can fortify...

1070
01:20:30.869 --> 01:20:32.496
...shore up. make safe.

1071
01:20:32.746 --> 01:20:33.914
Yes.

1072
01:20:35.582 --> 01:20:36.583
Yes...

1073
01:20:37.792 --> 01:20:38.793
...that is it.

1074
01:20:39.753 --> 01:20:41.755
We must move the gold
further underground...

1075
01:20:42.005 --> 01:20:43.381
- ...to safety.
- Did you hear me?

1076
01:20:43.632 --> 01:20:45.800
Dain is surrounded.

1077
01:20:46.051 --> 01:20:47.761
They're being slaughtered. Thorin.

1078
01:20:50.263 --> 01:20:51.723
Many die in war.

1079
01:20:52.974 --> 01:20:54.559
Life is cheap.

1080
01:20:56.686 --> 01:20:57.687
But a treasure...

1081
01:20:57.938 --> 01:20:59.898
...such as this cannot be counted...

1082
01:21:00.148 --> 01:21:01.816
...in lives lost.

1083
01:21:04.903 --> 01:21:06.404
It is worth...

1084
01:21:06.655 --> 01:21:09.157
...all the blood we can spend.

1085
01:21:10.825 --> 01:21:13.245
You sit here in these vast halls...

1086
01:21:13.495 --> 01:21:15.956
...with a crown upon your head...

1087
01:21:16.706 --> 01:21:19.793
...and yet you are lesser now
than you have ever been.

1088
01:21:21.628 --> 01:21:23.547
Do not speak to me...

1089
01:21:25.215 --> 01:21:27.259
...as if I were some lowly Dwarf Lord...

1090
01:21:29.135 --> 01:21:30.095
...as if...

1091
01:21:30.345 --> 01:21:32.806
...I were still...

1092
01:21:35.809 --> 01:21:37.310
...Thorin...

1093
01:21:38.019 --> 01:21:39.980
...Oakenshield.

1094
01:21:41.898 --> 01:21:44.484
- I am your king!
- You were always my king.

1095
01:21:44.901 --> 01:21:46.778
You used to know that once.

1096
01:21:48.113 --> 01:21:50.699
You cannot see what you have become.

1097
01:21:54.160 --> 01:21:55.370
Go.

1098
01:21:58.123 --> 01:21:59.416
Get out.

1099
01:22:01.918 --> 01:22:03.753
Before I kill you.

1100
01:22:18.310 --> 01:22:19.477
DWALIN:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">You sit here...</i></font>

1101
01:22:19.728 --> 01:22:22.564
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...with a crown upon your head.</i></font>

1102
01:22:22.814 --> 01:22:24.858
<i><font color="#80FFFF">You are lesser now
than you have ever been.</i></font>

1103
01:22:25.108 --> 01:22:29.112
THORIN: <i><font color="#80FFFF">But a treasure such as this</i></font>
<i><font color="#80FFFF">cannot be counted in lives lost.</i></font>

1104
01:22:29.362 --> 01:22:31.364
BALIN:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">A sickness lies upon that treasure.</i></font>

1105
01:22:31.615 --> 01:22:33.992
BARD:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">The blind ambition of a Mountain King.</i></font>

1106
01:22:34.242 --> 01:22:35.493
THORIN:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Am I not the king?</i></font>

1107
01:22:35.744 --> 01:22:37.078
<i><font color="#80FFFF">This gold...</i></font>

1108
01:22:37.329 --> 01:22:38.663
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...is ours.</i></font>

1109
01:22:38.913 --> 01:22:40.415
<i><font color="#80FFFF">And ours alone.</i></font>

1110
01:22:41.499 --> 01:22:44.044
<i><font color="#80FFFF">I will not part...</i></font>

1111
01:22:44.961 --> 01:22:47.213
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...with a single coin.</i></font>

1112
01:22:47.464 --> 01:22:49.257
BARD: <i><font color="#80FFFF">He could not see</i></font>
<i><font color="#80FFFF">beyond his own desire!</i></font>

1113
01:22:49.507 --> 01:22:52.010
THORIN:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">As if I were some lowly Dwarf Lord...</i></font>

1114
01:22:52.260 --> 01:22:54.346
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...Thorin Oakenshield.</i></font>

1115
01:22:54.596 --> 01:22:58.099
BALIN: <i><font color="#80FFFF">A sickness which drove</i></font>
<i><font color="#80FFFF">your grandfather mad.</i></font>

1116
01:22:58.350 --> 01:22:59.976
DWALIN:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">This is Thorin...</i></font>

1117
01:23:00.226 --> 01:23:02.854
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...son of Thrain. son of Thror!</i></font>

1118
01:23:03.104 --> 01:23:05.315
THORIN: <i><font color="#80FFFF">I am not my grandfather.</i></font>
<i><font color="#80FFFF">I am not my grandfather.</i></font>

1119
01:23:05.565 --> 01:23:07.484
GANDALF:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">You are the heir to the Throne of Durin.</i></font>

1120
01:23:07.734 --> 01:23:09.611
DWALIN:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">They are dying out there.</i></font>

1121
01:23:09.861 --> 01:23:11.071
GANDALF:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Take back Erebor.</i></font>

1122
01:23:11.321 --> 01:23:12.739
DWALIN:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Dain is surrounded.</i></font>

1123
01:23:12.989 --> 01:23:13.990
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Dying.</i></font>

1124
01:23:14.240 --> 01:23:15.241
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Is surrounded.</i></font>

1125
01:23:15.492 --> 01:23:16.493
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Dying.</i></font>

1126
01:23:16.743 --> 01:23:19.579
GANDALF:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Take back your homeland.</i></font>

1127
01:23:20.163 --> 01:23:22.332
BILBO:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">You are changed. Thorin.</i></font>

1128
01:23:22.582 --> 01:23:24.209
THORIN:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">I am not my grandfather.</i></font>

1129
01:23:24.459 --> 01:23:27.504
BILBO: <i><font color="#80FFFF">Is this treasure truly worth more</i></font>
<i><font color="#80FFFF">than your honor?</i></font>

1130
01:23:27.754 --> 01:23:29.881
THORIN:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">I am not my grandfather.</i></font>

1131
01:23:32.676 --> 01:23:34.052
[RUMBLING]

1132
01:23:42.936 --> 01:23:46.231
GANDALF:
<i><font color="#80FFFF">This treasure will be your death!</i></font>

1133
01:23:47.065 --> 01:23:48.692
[SCREAMS]

1134
01:23:59.285 --> 01:23:59.994
[SCREAMING]

1135
01:24:28.273 --> 01:24:29.399
Fall back!

1136
01:24:30.150 --> 01:24:31.192
Fall back...

1137
01:24:31.443 --> 01:24:33.111
...to the Mountain!

1138
01:24:35.822 --> 01:24:37.240
Fall back!

1139
01:24:41.035 --> 01:24:42.036
AZOG [IN BLACK SPEECH]:

1140
01:24:48.668 --> 01:24:50.670
[HORN BLOWING]

1141
01:25:19.783 --> 01:25:21.326
KILI:
I will not hide...

1142
01:25:21.576 --> 01:25:22.911
...behind a wall of stone...

1143
01:25:23.161 --> 01:25:26.080
...while others fight our battles for us!

1144
01:25:29.793 --> 01:25:32.212
It is not in my blood. Thorin.

1145
01:25:37.008 --> 01:25:38.384
No.

1146
01:25:38.635 --> 01:25:40.053
It is not.

1147
01:25:42.138 --> 01:25:44.349
We are sons of Durin.

1148
01:25:47.352 --> 01:25:48.853
And Durin's Folk...

1149
01:25:50.188 --> 01:25:52.649
...do not flee from a fight.

1150
01:26:15.588 --> 01:26:19.467
I have no right to ask this of any of you.

1151
01:26:24.472 --> 01:26:26.349
But will you follow me...

1152
01:26:27.767 --> 01:26:29.477
...one last time?

1153
01:26:39.988 --> 01:26:41.990
[ORC SHOUTING IN BLACK SPEECH]

1154
01:26:45.034 --> 01:26:47.036
[ALL SHOUT IN BLACK SPEECH]

1155
01:26:47.537 --> 01:26:48.788
[IN BLACK SPEECH]

1156
01:26:51.833 --> 01:26:53.334
[TROLLS ROAR]

1157
01:26:56.004 --> 01:26:57.630
[HORN BLOWING]

1158
01:26:59.090 --> 01:27:00.592
[HORN BLOWING]

1159
01:27:10.560 --> 01:27:11.394
Thorin.

1160
01:27:19.861 --> 01:27:21.070
[BELL RINGING]

1161
01:27:27.327 --> 01:27:28.578
[ALL SHOUTING]

1162
01:27:37.629 --> 01:27:40.131
DAIN:
To the king!

1163
01:27:41.090 --> 01:27:42.967
To the king!

1164
01:27:45.637 --> 01:27:47.847
[SHOUTING IN DWARVISH]

1165
01:28:06.741 --> 01:28:07.742
The Dwarves.

1166
01:28:08.534 --> 01:28:09.827
They're rallying.

1167
01:28:12.997 --> 01:28:15.208
They're rallying to their king.

1168
01:28:19.212 --> 01:28:21.673
Any man who wants to give their last...

1169
01:28:22.340 --> 01:28:23.841
...follow me!

1170
01:28:24.092 --> 01:28:25.510
[ALL SHOUTING]

1171
01:28:42.276 --> 01:28:45.989
I say we stand with our men
in life and in death.

1172
01:28:46.239 --> 01:28:47.782
- I'm with you.
HILDA: Arm yourselves.

1173
01:28:49.659 --> 01:28:50.910
- Come with us.
WOMAN: No. no. no.

1174
01:28:51.160 --> 01:28:53.496
- You leave an old woman be.
- Don't be afraid.

1175
01:28:53.746 --> 01:28:54.998
WOMAN [IN DEEP VOICE]:
I said. get off!

1176
01:28:56.749 --> 01:28:58.418
Alfrid Lickspittle.

1177
01:28:58.668 --> 01:28:59.585
You are a coward.

1178
01:28:59.836 --> 01:29:00.837
"Coward"?

1179
01:29:01.087 --> 01:29:03.506
Not every man's brave enough
to wear a corset.

1180
01:29:03.756 --> 01:29:04.924
You're not a man.

1181
01:29:05.174 --> 01:29:06.759
You're a weasel.

1182
01:29:07.010 --> 01:29:08.845
[CHATTERING]

1183
01:29:21.190 --> 01:29:22.233
Dain!

1184
01:29:23.151 --> 01:29:24.277
Thorin!

1185
01:29:25.278 --> 01:29:26.320
Hold on!

1186
01:29:26.571 --> 01:29:27.822
I'm coming!

1187
01:29:28.823 --> 01:29:30.116
[YELLS]

1188
01:29:35.288 --> 01:29:36.664
Hey. cousin!

1189
01:29:38.666 --> 01:29:39.333
What took you so long?

1190
01:29:40.501 --> 01:29:41.252
[LAUGHING]

1191
01:29:44.255 --> 01:29:46.257
There's too many of these buggers. Thorin.

1192
01:29:47.258 --> 01:29:48.426
I hope you've got a plan.

1193
01:29:49.927 --> 01:29:51.054
THORIN:
Aye.

1194
01:29:51.929 --> 01:29:53.765
We're going to take out their leader.

1195
01:29:54.515 --> 01:29:55.558
Azog?

1196
01:29:59.312 --> 01:30:01.814
I'm gonna kill that piece of filth.

1197
01:30:02.065 --> 01:30:02.940
Lead on!

1198
01:30:13.951 --> 01:30:14.952
[GROANS]

1199
01:30:17.830 --> 01:30:20.166
We may yet survive this.

1200
01:30:21.542 --> 01:30:22.376
Gandalf!

1201
01:30:30.343 --> 01:30:31.052
It's Thorin.

1202
01:30:32.095 --> 01:30:33.137
And Fili. Kili...

1203
01:30:33.763 --> 01:30:35.139
...and Dwalin.

1204
01:30:36.182 --> 01:30:38.184
He's taking his best warriors.

1205
01:30:38.434 --> 01:30:39.644
To do what?

1206
01:30:40.520 --> 01:30:42.897
To cut the head off the snake.

1207
01:31:04.043 --> 01:31:04.752
[YELLS]

1208
01:31:16.681 --> 01:31:17.431
Die!

1209
01:31:24.689 --> 01:31:26.065
[IN ENGLISH]
Gandalf!

1210
01:31:26.774 --> 01:31:27.984
Legolas.

1211
01:31:29.610 --> 01:31:30.778
Legolas Greenleaf.

1212
01:31:31.028 --> 01:31:32.238
There is a second army.

1213
01:31:32.488 --> 01:31:35.449
Bolg leads a force of Gundabad Orcs.
They are almost upon us.

1214
01:31:35.700 --> 01:31:37.160
Gundabad.

1215
01:31:38.369 --> 01:31:40.037
This was their plan all along.

1216
01:31:42.748 --> 01:31:46.210
Azog engages our forces.
then Bolg sweeps in from the North.

1217
01:31:46.460 --> 01:31:47.837
The North?

1218
01:31:48.087 --> 01:31:49.422
Where is the North...

1219
01:31:49.672 --> 01:31:51.757
- ...exactly?
- Ravenhill.

1220
01:31:52.967 --> 01:31:54.010
Ravenhill?

1221
01:31:54.260 --> 01:31:55.928
Thorin is up there.

1222
01:31:56.179 --> 01:31:58.181
And Fili and Kili. They're all up there.

1223
01:32:14.405 --> 01:32:15.781
KILI:
Where is he?

1224
01:32:20.995 --> 01:32:22.413
It looks empty.

1225
01:32:23.873 --> 01:32:25.583
I think Azog has fled.

1226
01:32:26.834 --> 01:32:28.461
I don't think so.

1227
01:32:31.172 --> 01:32:32.173
Fili...

1228
01:32:33.382 --> 01:32:34.759
...take your brother.

1229
01:32:35.009 --> 01:32:36.260
Scout out the towers.

1230
01:32:37.136 --> 01:32:38.846
Keep low and out of sight.

1231
01:32:39.096 --> 01:32:40.139
If you see something...

1232
01:32:40.389 --> 01:32:41.557
...report back. Do not engage.

1233
01:32:41.807 --> 01:32:44.018
- Do you understand?
- We have company.

1234
01:32:44.268 --> 01:32:45.061
[GOBLINS GRUNTING]

1235
01:32:45.311 --> 01:32:46.687
Goblin mercenaries.

1236
01:32:46.938 --> 01:32:48.272
No more than a hundred.

1237
01:32:48.522 --> 01:32:50.149
We'll take care of them. Go!

1238
01:32:50.399 --> 01:32:51.567
Go!

1239
01:32:53.152 --> 01:32:54.487
DWALIN:
Come on!

1240
01:33:22.848 --> 01:33:24.392
Recall your company.

1241
01:33:25.685 --> 01:33:27.561
[HORN BLOWING]

1242
01:33:30.523 --> 01:33:32.358
My lord. dispatch this force...

1243
01:33:32.608 --> 01:33:34.402
...to Ravenhill.
The Dwarves are about...

1244
01:33:34.652 --> 01:33:35.444
...to be overrun.

1245
01:33:35.695 --> 01:33:36.529
Thorin must be warned.

1246
01:33:36.779 --> 01:33:39.031
By all means. warn him.

1247
01:33:39.282 --> 01:33:41.617
I have spent enough Elvish blood
in defense...

1248
01:33:41.867 --> 01:33:43.286
...of this accursed land. No more.

1249
01:33:43.536 --> 01:33:44.996
Thranduil?

1250
01:33:45.997 --> 01:33:46.706
I'll go.

1251
01:33:47.873 --> 01:33:48.958
Don't be ridiculous.

1252
01:33:49.208 --> 01:33:50.626
You'll never make it.

1253
01:33:50.876 --> 01:33:51.544
Why not?

1254
01:33:52.420 --> 01:33:54.964
Because they will see you coming
and kill you.

1255
01:33:55.840 --> 01:33:57.174
No. they won't.

1256
01:33:58.718 --> 01:33:59.677
They won't see me.

1257
01:34:01.053 --> 01:34:02.722
It's out of the question.

1258
01:34:03.723 --> 01:34:04.724
I won't allow it.

1259
01:34:05.725 --> 01:34:08.144
I'm not asking you to allow it. Gandalf.

1260
01:34:44.889 --> 01:34:46.599
TAURIEL [IN ELVISH]:

1261
01:34:46.849 --> 01:34:48.976
[IN ENGLISH]
You will not turn away.

1262
01:34:49.643 --> 01:34:50.728
Not this time.

1263
01:34:51.395 --> 01:34:53.564
Get out of my way.

1264
01:34:53.814 --> 01:34:55.399
The Dwarves will be slaughtered.

1265
01:34:55.649 --> 01:34:57.693
Yes. they will die.

1266
01:34:58.527 --> 01:34:59.820
Today...

1267
01:35:00.613 --> 01:35:01.655
...tomorrow...

1268
01:35:01.906 --> 01:35:04.408
...one year hence.
a hundred years from now.

1269
01:35:05.117 --> 01:35:06.619
What does it matter?

1270
01:35:07.328 --> 01:35:08.371
They are mortal.

1271
01:35:11.582 --> 01:35:13.417
You think your life is worth more...

1272
01:35:14.001 --> 01:35:16.212
...when there is no love in it?

1273
01:35:16.879 --> 01:35:20.007
There is no love in you.

1274
01:35:26.931 --> 01:35:28.099
What do you know of love?

1275
01:35:28.349 --> 01:35:29.058
Nothing.

1276
01:35:30.351 --> 01:35:31.477
What you feel for that Dwarf...

1277
01:35:31.727 --> 01:35:33.020
...is not real.

1278
01:35:35.398 --> 01:35:36.899
You think it is love?

1279
01:35:37.775 --> 01:35:39.944
Are you ready to die for it?

1280
01:35:43.239 --> 01:35:44.740
LEGOLAS [IN ELVISH]:

1281
01:35:53.416 --> 01:35:54.875
[IN ENGLISH]
I will go with you.

1282
01:36:06.011 --> 01:36:06.887
[ROARS]

1283
01:36:10.724 --> 01:36:11.559
[SCREAMS]

1284
01:36:17.022 --> 01:36:18.190
Get up.

1285
01:36:18.774 --> 01:36:19.984
Get away from me.

1286
01:36:20.234 --> 01:36:21.527
I don't take orders...

1287
01:36:21.777 --> 01:36:23.237
...from you.
People trusted you.

1288
01:36:23.487 --> 01:36:24.655
They listened to you.

1289
01:36:24.905 --> 01:36:25.906
The Master's mantle...

1290
01:36:26.157 --> 01:36:28.242
...was there for the taking...

1291
01:36:29.326 --> 01:36:30.661
...and you threw it all away.

1292
01:36:31.537 --> 01:36:32.955
For what?

1293
01:36:41.630 --> 01:36:42.715
BARD:
Alfrid...

1294
01:36:42.965 --> 01:36:44.425
...your slip is showing.

1295
01:36:56.687 --> 01:36:57.730
[CREATURE ROARS]

1296
01:36:58.731 --> 01:37:00.608
Hey. Stay here.

1297
01:37:00.858 --> 01:37:02.485
Search the lower levels.

1298
01:37:03.527 --> 01:37:05.029
I've got this.

1299
01:37:14.079 --> 01:37:16.040
Where is that Orc filth?

1300
01:37:18.209 --> 01:37:19.418
Thorin.

1301
01:37:20.002 --> 01:37:21.170
Bilbo.

1302
01:37:21.420 --> 01:37:23.047
You have to leave here. Now.

1303
01:37:23.297 --> 01:37:25.257
Azog has an army attacking
from the North.

1304
01:37:25.508 --> 01:37:27.176
This watchtower will be surrounded.

1305
01:37:27.426 --> 01:37:29.261
- With no way out.
- We are so close.

1306
01:37:29.512 --> 01:37:31.514
That Orc scum is in there.
I say we push on.

1307
01:37:31.764 --> 01:37:34.308
No. That's what he wants.

1308
01:37:34.558 --> 01:37:36.227
He wants to draw us in.

1309
01:37:38.312 --> 01:37:39.480
This is a trap.

1310
01:37:46.695 --> 01:37:47.905
[SNIFFS]

1311
01:37:48.155 --> 01:37:49.490
Ah.

1312
01:37:49.823 --> 01:37:51.825
[CREATURE ROARS]

1313
01:37:52.368 --> 01:37:54.328
[RUMBLING]

1314
01:37:55.538 --> 01:37:57.248
Find Fili and Kili. Call them back.

1315
01:37:57.498 --> 01:37:58.999
Thorin. are you sure about this?

1316
01:37:59.250 --> 01:38:00.334
Do it.

1317
01:38:02.169 --> 01:38:03.879
We'll live to fight another day.

1318
01:38:09.510 --> 01:38:10.844
[DRUM BEATING]

1319
01:38:23.065 --> 01:38:24.400
[GRUNTING]

1320
01:38:25.943 --> 01:38:26.986
Oh...

1321
01:38:27.486 --> 01:38:29.321
AZOG [IN BLACK SPEECH]:

1322
01:38:39.582 --> 01:38:40.165
Go.

1323
01:38:44.795 --> 01:38:45.462
Run!

1324
01:38:46.088 --> 01:38:46.922
[GROANS]

1325
01:39:04.023 --> 01:39:05.649
[GRUNTS]

1326
01:39:07.276 --> 01:39:08.652
[GRUNTING]

1327
01:39:15.993 --> 01:39:17.161
Kili!

1328
01:39:17.995 --> 01:39:19.079
DWALIN:
Thorin.

1329
01:39:21.832 --> 01:39:23.250
Thorin. No.

1330
01:39:47.691 --> 01:39:48.734
[ROARING]

1331
01:39:48.984 --> 01:39:50.319
[YELLING AND GRUNTING]

1332
01:40:18.430 --> 01:40:20.599
[SCREECHING]

1333
01:40:30.484 --> 01:40:32.069
[SHOUTING IN BLACK SPEECH]

1334
01:40:33.070 --> 01:40:33.737
[ALL SHOUTING]

1335
01:40:41.745 --> 01:40:42.830
[IN BLACK SPEECH]

1336
01:40:46.667 --> 01:40:47.668
No.

1337
01:40:51.839 --> 01:40:53.382
[ALL SHOUTING]

1338
01:41:04.601 --> 01:41:05.602
TAURIEL:
Kili.

1339
01:42:10.292 --> 01:42:11.084
[GRUNTS]

1340
01:42:37.110 --> 01:42:38.654
[IN BLACK SPEECH]

1341
01:43:05.931 --> 01:43:06.932
Kili!

1342
01:43:11.979 --> 01:43:12.980
Kili!

1343
01:43:13.230 --> 01:43:14.064
Tauriel!

1344
01:43:15.649 --> 01:43:16.650
Kili.

1345
01:43:16.900 --> 01:43:17.651
[ROARS]

1346
01:43:18.527 --> 01:43:19.361
[GROANS]

1347
01:43:33.000 --> 01:43:33.500
[GROANS]

1348
01:43:40.674 --> 01:43:41.633
[CHOKING]

1349
01:43:47.222 --> 01:43:48.348
[TAURIEL YELLS]

1350
01:43:49.474 --> 01:43:50.100
[GRUNTS]

1351
01:44:21.757 --> 01:44:22.674
No!

1352
01:44:33.477 --> 01:44:34.269
No!

1353
01:45:29.866 --> 01:45:30.951
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1354
01:46:00.355 --> 01:46:01.940
[TAURIEL GASPS AND COUGHS]

1355
01:48:33.300 --> 01:48:34.759
[HORN BLOWING]

1356
01:48:38.221 --> 01:48:39.431
[RUMBLING]

1357
01:48:39.681 --> 01:48:41.308
Mm.

1358
01:48:44.060 --> 01:48:44.811
[ROARS]

1359
01:48:59.701 --> 01:49:00.452
[ROARS]

1360
01:49:48.583 --> 01:49:49.834
Tauriel!

1361
01:50:53.189 --> 01:50:55.191
[SQUAWKING]

1362
01:51:12.000 --> 01:51:12.500
[ROARING]

1363
01:52:47.262 --> 01:52:48.847
[SCREAMS]

1364
01:53:01.860 --> 01:53:02.694
[SNARLS]

1365
01:53:14.122 --> 01:53:15.665
[GRUNTS]

1366
01:53:28.553 --> 01:53:29.888
[GROANS]

1367
01:53:32.974 --> 01:53:34.809
[GROANING]

1368
01:54:28.238 --> 01:54:29.239
[SQUAWKING]

1369
01:54:31.491 --> 01:54:33.368
The Eagles are coming.

1370
01:55:21.165 --> 01:55:22.000
[COUGHING AND GASPING]

1371
01:55:23.668 --> 01:55:24.460
Bilbo.

1372
01:55:24.711 --> 01:55:26.671
Don't move. Don't move. Lie still.

1373
01:55:28.339 --> 01:55:30.883
Oh. Mm. Mm.

1374
01:55:31.259 --> 01:55:32.385
I'm glad you are here.

1375
01:55:32.635 --> 01:55:34.178
- Shh. shh.
- Unh.

1376
01:55:35.138 --> 01:55:36.931
I wish to part from you in friendship.

1377
01:55:37.181 --> 01:55:38.016
No.

1378
01:55:38.266 --> 01:55:39.642
You are not going anywhere.

1379
01:55:40.393 --> 01:55:41.728
You're going to live.

1380
01:55:42.186 --> 01:55:43.187
I would take back...

1381
01:55:43.438 --> 01:55:45.273
...my words and my deeds at the Gate.

1382
01:55:47.108 --> 01:55:49.527
You did what only a true friend would do.

1383
01:55:50.987 --> 01:55:51.988
Forgive me.

1384
01:55:54.782 --> 01:55:56.868
I was too blind to see it.

1385
01:55:59.245 --> 01:56:00.788
I am so sorry...

1386
01:56:02.165 --> 01:56:04.042
...that I have led you into such peril.

1387
01:56:05.209 --> 01:56:07.962
No. I'm glad to have shared
in your perils. Thorin.

1388
01:56:08.212 --> 01:56:09.505
Each and every one of them.

1389
01:56:12.925 --> 01:56:15.887
It is far more than any Baggins deserves.

1390
01:56:20.308 --> 01:56:21.309
Farewell...

1391
01:56:22.435 --> 01:56:24.228
...Master Burglar.

1392
01:56:25.563 --> 01:56:27.607
Go back to your books.

1393
01:56:28.775 --> 01:56:30.777
And your armchair.

1394
01:56:32.528 --> 01:56:34.447
Plant your trees.

1395
01:56:35.114 --> 01:56:36.783
Watch them grow.

1396
01:56:38.242 --> 01:56:39.535
[GROANS]

1397
01:56:41.829 --> 01:56:43.581
If more people...

1398
01:56:44.624 --> 01:56:46.250
...valued home...

1399
01:56:46.501 --> 01:56:48.461
...above gold...

1400
01:56:49.462 --> 01:56:53.049
...this world would be a merrier place.

1401
01:56:55.176 --> 01:56:56.219
[GRUNTS]

1402
01:56:56.719 --> 01:56:59.013
No. No. no. no. No.

1403
01:56:59.263 --> 01:57:01.683
Thorin. Thorin. don't you dare.

1404
01:57:03.976 --> 01:57:05.103
Thorin.

1405
01:57:11.067 --> 01:57:13.444
Thorin. Thorin. hold on.

1406
01:57:13.695 --> 01:57:14.862
Hold on. please.

1407
01:57:15.405 --> 01:57:16.572
The Eagles...

1408
01:57:17.240 --> 01:57:19.450
The Eagles... The Eagles are here.

1409
01:57:20.118 --> 01:57:21.285
Thorin?

1410
01:57:24.497 --> 01:57:25.623
The Ea...

1411
01:57:27.125 --> 01:57:29.127
[SOBBING]

1412
01:57:42.807 --> 01:57:44.809
[SNIFFLING]

1413
01:58:22.263 --> 01:58:24.891
I cannot go back.

1414
01:58:25.933 --> 01:58:26.934
Where will you go?

1415
01:58:29.061 --> 01:58:30.563
I do not know.

1416
01:58:31.814 --> 01:58:33.232
Go north.

1417
01:58:33.858 --> 01:58:35.443
Find the Dúnedain.

1418
01:58:36.986 --> 01:58:40.239
There's a young Ranger amongst them.
You should meet him.

1419
01:58:42.408 --> 01:58:44.702
His father. Arathorn. was a good man.

1420
01:58:45.286 --> 01:58:46.662
His son...

1421
01:58:47.330 --> 01:58:49.499
...might grow to be a great one.

1422
01:58:52.335 --> 01:58:53.336
What is his name?

1423
01:58:54.378 --> 01:58:56.756
He's known in the Wild as Strider.

1424
01:58:57.632 --> 01:58:59.258
His true name...

1425
01:58:59.509 --> 01:59:01.928
...you must discover for yourself.

1426
01:59:05.973 --> 01:59:07.225
Legolas.

1427
01:59:08.893 --> 01:59:10.645
Your mother loved you.

1428
01:59:12.980 --> 01:59:14.607
More than anyone.

1429
01:59:15.566 --> 01:59:17.193
More than life.

1430
01:59:52.979 --> 01:59:54.897
They want to bury him.

1431
01:59:56.941 --> 01:59:58.109
Yes.

1432
01:59:59.610 --> 02:00:02.405
If this is love. I do not want it.

1433
02:00:05.783 --> 02:00:07.535
Take it from me.

1434
02:00:08.286 --> 02:00:09.871
Please.

1435
02:00:15.334 --> 02:00:17.962
[VOICE BREAKING]
Why does it hurt so much?

1436
02:00:19.005 --> 02:00:21.048
Because it was real.

1437
02:01:02.506 --> 02:01:04.133
[SIGHS]

1438
02:02:25.840 --> 02:02:27.550
[HORNS BLOWING]

1439
02:03:06.380 --> 02:03:08.549
BALIN:
There is to be a great feast tonight.

1440
02:03:08.799 --> 02:03:12.053
Songs will be sung. Tales will be told.

1441
02:03:14.055 --> 02:03:16.182
And Thorin Oakenshield...

1442
02:03:16.432 --> 02:03:18.476
...will pass into legend.

1443
02:03:19.810 --> 02:03:21.520
I know that's how you must honor him.

1444
02:03:21.771 --> 02:03:23.647
But to me. he was never that.

1445
02:03:24.857 --> 02:03:26.108
He was...

1446
02:03:27.485 --> 02:03:28.778
To me...

1447
02:03:30.571 --> 02:03:31.822
...he was...

1448
02:03:39.038 --> 02:03:41.999
I'll slip quietly away.
Will you tell the others I said goodbye?

1449
02:03:42.249 --> 02:03:44.043
You can tell them yourself.

1450
02:04:00.351 --> 02:04:03.687
If any of you are ever passing Bag End. uh...

1451
02:04:08.776 --> 02:04:10.069
...tea is at 4.

1452
02:04:11.695 --> 02:04:13.280
There's plenty of it.

1453
02:04:15.908 --> 02:04:17.827
You are welcome anytime.

1454
02:04:23.791 --> 02:04:25.167
Uh...

1455
02:04:26.585 --> 02:04:28.087
Don't bother knocking.

1456
02:04:28.337 --> 02:04:29.588
[ALL CHUCKLE]

1457
02:05:09.170 --> 02:05:10.421
[GANDALF CHUCKLES]

1458
02:05:10.671 --> 02:05:12.840
GANDALF:
Ah. the borders of the Shire.

1459
02:05:14.800 --> 02:05:16.594
It is here I must leave you.

1460
02:05:19.263 --> 02:05:20.639
That's a shame.

1461
02:05:23.184 --> 02:05:24.852
I quite liked having...

1462
02:05:25.102 --> 02:05:26.812
...a Wizard around.

1463
02:05:28.063 --> 02:05:29.815
Seems they bring good luck.

1464
02:05:30.900 --> 02:05:34.278
You don't really suppose. do you.
that all your adventures and escapes...

1465
02:05:34.528 --> 02:05:36.697
...were managed by mere luck?

1466
02:05:37.698 --> 02:05:40.868
Magic rings should not be used lightly.
Bilbo.

1467
02:05:41.118 --> 02:05:42.411
Don't take me for a fool.

1468
02:05:42.661 --> 02:05:45.122
I know you found one in the Goblin tunnels.

1469
02:05:45.372 --> 02:05:47.416
And I've kept my eye on you...

1470
02:05:47.666 --> 02:05:48.751
...ever since.

1471
02:05:51.921 --> 02:05:53.505
Well. thank goodness.

1472
02:05:58.219 --> 02:05:59.845
Farewell. Gandalf.

1473
02:06:02.765 --> 02:06:04.183
Farewell.

1474
02:06:11.357 --> 02:06:12.608
You. uh...

1475
02:06:12.858 --> 02:06:16.487
You needn't worry about that ring.
Fell out of my pocket during the battle.

1476
02:06:16.737 --> 02:06:17.821
I lost it.

1477
02:06:18.739 --> 02:06:22.034
You're a very fine person. Mr. Baggins.

1478
02:06:22.993 --> 02:06:23.994
And I'm very fond...

1479
02:06:24.245 --> 02:06:25.412
...of you.

1480
02:06:27.122 --> 02:06:29.458
But you're only quite a little fellow...

1481
02:06:30.709 --> 02:06:33.545
...in a wide world after all.

1482
02:06:51.814 --> 02:06:53.357
[HOBBITS CHATTERING]

1483
02:07:04.827 --> 02:07:07.705
Wait a minute.
that's my mother's glory box.

1484
02:07:07.955 --> 02:07:10.249
And that's my dining chair.

1485
02:07:10.499 --> 02:07:13.502
Ah... Put that pouf down!

1486
02:07:13.752 --> 02:07:15.254
What is going on?

1487
02:07:15.838 --> 02:07:16.714
WORRYWORT:
Hello...

1488
02:07:16.964 --> 02:07:17.840
...Mr. Bilbo.

1489
02:07:18.090 --> 02:07:19.717
You're not supposed to be here.

1490
02:07:19.967 --> 02:07:21.593
What do you mean?

1491
02:07:21.844 --> 02:07:23.429
On account of you
being presumed dead.

1492
02:07:24.388 --> 02:07:25.848
I am not dead.

1493
02:07:26.098 --> 02:07:27.933
Presumed or otherwise.

1494
02:07:29.059 --> 02:07:30.978
WORRYWORT:
I'm not sure that's permitted.

1495
02:07:31.228 --> 02:07:32.813
Mr. Bilbo!

1496
02:07:33.063 --> 02:07:35.482
TOSSER:
Twenty-one! Any advance on 21?

1497
02:07:35.733 --> 02:07:37.484
Any advance on 21?

1498
02:07:37.860 --> 02:07:40.612
Ha. ha! Sold to Mrs. Bolger.

1499
02:07:40.863 --> 02:07:43.240
Somewhere for Fatty to put his feet on.

1500
02:07:44.116 --> 02:07:45.117
[ALL LAUGHING]

1501
02:07:45.367 --> 02:07:46.410
Any bids for this?

1502
02:07:46.660 --> 02:07:48.996
This is Shire-made.

1503
02:07:49.246 --> 02:07:51.040
No Dwarvish reproductions here.

1504
02:07:51.290 --> 02:07:52.291
BILBO:
Stop!

1505
02:07:52.541 --> 02:07:53.792
Stop!

1506
02:07:54.043 --> 02:07:56.086
- There's been a mistake!
LOBELIA: Who are you?

1507
02:07:56.337 --> 02:07:57.338
Who am I?

1508
02:07:57.588 --> 02:07:59.048
You know who I am...

1509
02:07:59.298 --> 02:08:01.133
...Lobelia Sackville-Baggins.

1510
02:08:01.383 --> 02:08:02.760
This is my home.

1511
02:08:03.010 --> 02:08:05.262
And those are my spoons.
Thank you very much.

1512
02:08:05.512 --> 02:08:07.139
TOSSER: This is most irregular.
- Excuse me.

1513
02:08:07.389 --> 02:08:08.223
TOSSER:
It's been more...

1514
02:08:08.474 --> 02:08:10.768
...than 13 months since the disappearance.

1515
02:08:11.018 --> 02:08:12.644
If you are in fact...

1516
02:08:12.895 --> 02:08:15.939
...Bilbo Baggins and undeceased...

1517
02:08:16.190 --> 02:08:17.733
...can you prove it?

1518
02:08:17.983 --> 02:08:18.776
What?

1519
02:08:19.026 --> 02:08:20.652
Something official with your name...

1520
02:08:20.903 --> 02:08:21.987
...on it would suffice.

1521
02:08:22.237 --> 02:08:24.114
All right. Right.

1522
02:08:24.365 --> 02:08:26.283
[CROWD MURMURING]

1523
02:08:26.992 --> 02:08:29.286
A contract of employment as a bur...

1524
02:08:31.955 --> 02:08:32.956
Never mind as what.

1525
02:08:34.917 --> 02:08:36.293
There. My signature.

1526
02:08:36.543 --> 02:08:38.545
Yes. well... Uh...

1527
02:08:38.796 --> 02:08:40.631
Well. it certainly seems to be in order.

1528
02:08:40.881 --> 02:08:42.007
Yes.

1529
02:08:42.257 --> 02:08:44.301
Seems there can be no doubt.

1530
02:08:45.260 --> 02:08:47.137
Who is this you pledged
your service to?

1531
02:08:49.181 --> 02:08:50.724
Thorin Oakenshield?

1532
02:08:54.186 --> 02:08:55.187
He...

1533
02:08:56.271 --> 02:08:57.815
He was my friend.

1534
02:10:49.426 --> 02:10:50.928
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

1535
02:10:52.638 --> 02:10:54.056
No. thank you!

1536
02:10:54.306 --> 02:10:56.475
We don't want any more visitors.
well-wishers...

1537
02:10:56.725 --> 02:10:58.936
...or distant relations!

1538
02:10:59.186 --> 02:11:00.270
GANDALF:
And what about...

1539
02:11:00.521 --> 02:11:02.272
...very old friends?

1540
02:11:09.863 --> 02:11:10.822
BILBO:
Gandalf?

1541
02:11:11.073 --> 02:11:12.366
GANDALF:
Bilbo Baggins.

1542
02:11:12.616 --> 02:11:14.576
BILBO:
My dear Gandalf! Ha. ha!

1543
02:11:14.826 --> 02:11:16.036
GANDALF:
It's good to see you.

1544
02:11:16.286 --> 02:11:19.873
One hundred and 11 years old.
Who would believe it?

1545
02:11:20.832 --> 02:11:22.417
[BOTH LAUGHING]

1546
02:11:24.086 --> 02:11:26.046
BILBO:
Come on. come in!

1547
02:11:26.296 --> 02:11:28.590
Welcome. Welcome.

1548
02:24:24.115 --> 02:24:26.117
[English - US - SDH]

1549
00:00:00.650 --> 00:00:02.150
